title: cream puff
directions: Boil 1 cup water and stick of butter.
Add flour.
Stir until thick.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake
30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: sopapillas
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out dough on floured cutting board.
Shape in 5-inch circles 1/8-inch thick and deep fry in very hot oil.
Move sopaipilla around so the dough begins to puff up.

title: fried pies
directions: Combine apricots, sugar and water in a medium saucepan and cook until apricots are tender; set aside.
Mix the cream cheese and butter together.
Sift flour and salt together and blend in cream cheese-butter mixture until thoroughly mixed.
Chill several hours or until dough is easy to handle.
Roll dough thin and cut in circles with an empty coffee can.
Place 1 to 2 teaspoons of apricot mixture in center of each circle.
Fold over and pinch edge together with fork.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar glaze, if desired.
Makes approximately 26 pies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Add next 7 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, for about 45 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole; alternating noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat mixture until all is used.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together the eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients in order.
Better if you sift the dry ingredients together before adding.
Fold in the zucchini and walnuts last. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour in mixed bread.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pans for about 5 minutes, then turn out and finish cooling.
Wrap in foil to store.
Freezes well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs good.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add Karo, melted butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into deep pie shell and bake slowly.

title: double-stuffed eggs
directions: The potato flakes make a full-bodied filling. One basic recipe with several variations to chill overnight.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage fine and cook in salted water for 5 to 7 minutes. Drain it. Next, make a sauce of the first 3 ingredients. Place first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan and let come to a boil. May add 2 tablespoons of water, if needed. Put cabbage in and boil quickly for about 5 minutes. Taste and season.

title: frit-o-que(free-tokie)
directions: Pour 1 cup chili con carne in casserole dish.
Add layer of grated cheese and chopped onion and layer of corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hi protein energy bars
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in milk.
Add dry milk crystals, wheat germ, flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat until well combined.
Fold in peanut butter chips and raisins.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars and wrap individually in foil or plastic wrap.

title: no knead bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together the flour and sugar.
Make a well in center; add oil and yeast water.
Mix dough.
It should form elastic-like strands when pulled from bowl. Pat top of dough with oil.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: aunt ginny's cheesecake
directions: For shell, grind cookies and combine butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Press into buttered spring-form pan, bottom and sides.
For mixture, cream 1 cup sugar and cream cheese; add flour, salt, vanilla and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well on medium speed.
Add milk; fold in beaten egg white.
Bake 1 hour at 275° to 300°.
Turn oven off and leave cake in for 1 hour with door closed.
Open the door and leave cake in for another hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in bowl; add eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: white chocolate saltines
directions: Place candy coating in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until coating melts.
Remove from heat.
Cool 2 minutes.
Add peanuts and pretzel sticks; stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill 20 minutes or until firm.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Put whites in large bowl until room temperature (1 hour).
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Grease 10 inch tube pan.
Beat at high speed, yolks with crisco and margarine.
Gradually add sugar, beat until light and fluffy.
At low speed beat in flour alternately with milk, ending with flour; add coconut.
Beat until well blended.
Beat egg whites just until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter until well blended.
Bake at 300 degrees for 2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: tuna-stuffed artichokes(makes 8 appetizer servings)
directions: With kitchen shears trim sharp points from artichoke leaves. Trim stems; remove loose outer leaves.
Cut 1-inch from the tops. Brush cut edges with lemon juice.
In a large covered saucepan or Dutch oven, bring artichokes and salted water to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer until a leaf pulls out easily, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain upside down.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour and cheese, beating until smooth.
Pour apples (drained) into buttered 9-inch dish. Top with cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes, until browned.
Serves 8.

title: orange rum yum cake
directions: Prepare pound cake mixes together according to package directions, adding the orange and lemon peel.
Turn into a greased and lightly floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cooling rack and cool for 20 minutes more.
Place on serving plate.
Using long-tined fork or skewer, punch holes in top of cake at 1-inch intervals.

title: peach salad
directions: Prepare jello with 2 cups boiling water and liquid from peaches.
Refrigerate until partially gelled.
Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together with mixer until well blended.
Then beat into jello.
Cut peaches into small pieces and stir (do not beat) into mixture.
Then pour into molds or large Pyrex rectangular dish.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces in 2 (9 x 12-inch) glass cake pans.
Beat 3 cups of milk together with 2 to 3 eggs.
Add sugar, raisins and seasoning and pour 1/2 over each pan.
Put raisins and nutmeg on top.
Beat rest of eggs and milk and pour over mixture. Allow to stand about 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 24 servings.

title: pineapple-cheese boat
directions: Cut pineapple lengthwise into quarters through green top.
Cut along edges of quarters to remove fruit.
Cut pineapple core off of fruit, and cut fruit into bite-sized pieces.
Place pineapple chunks, halved strawberries and melon balls into a large bowl. Sprinkle with ginger and lime juice; toss.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon fruit mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Spoon yogurt onto each serving, and garnish with whole strawberries.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, cumin seed, chili powder and minced garlic.
Simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Add rice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over corn chips.
Garnish with cheese, chopped black olives, chopped green onions, diced avocado and chopped green pepper.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese together. Grease casserole dish and fill with Veg-All mixture.
Crumble Ritz crackers, drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Boil chicken breast in 2 cups boiling water until completely done.
Remove chicken breast and add uncooked rice in the same pot of water.
After rice has cooked, pour into a bowl.
Dice cooked chicken breast, celery and green onion into bowl with rice.
Add curry powder to taste, then stir in mayonnaise.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours or overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly
1/2 cup soup and remaining ingredients.
Shape mix into a loaf.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Blend remaining soup, 1 1/4 cups water and 2 tablespoons drippings.
Heat.
Stir often.
Serve with loaf.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Slice bananas in pie crust.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over bananas.
Set in refrigerator and chill.
Whip cream and pour over other mixture.
Spoon blueberry filing on top of whipped cream.
Chill again before serving.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix the raspberries, marshmallows and sugar together; let stand for 1 hour.
Make jello according to package directions. Put in fridge; let it thicken slightly.
Whip jello; fold into berry mixture and 1 cup whipped cream.
Put into a baked pie shell; put in refrigerator.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add onion; cook 2 to 3 minutes, until tender.
Add turkey, stirring constantly over medium heat until turkey is no longer pink.
Stir in salsa, spices and cornstarch mixture; heat through and simmer to thicken.
Serve on corn or wheat tortillas; garnish with 1 tablespoon fat-free sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: Melt all margarine.
Stir in cocoa, sugar, flour, vanilla and eggs (one at a time), beating eggs slightly.
Pour mixture into foil cups, filling cups 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Makes 24 to 36 cups.

title: mexican hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make small balls, which are much better.
Will feed 7 to 8 people.
Add 2 or 3 peppers to make it hotter.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Meat Prep:
Brown ground beef, adding spices or you can make meatballs by adding spices and seasoned bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly. Roll into meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 350° until browned. Add to sauce.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Cut yams and apples in 1/2-inch slices.
Layer in buttered 3-quart deep casserole dish, starting with apples and ending with yams.
Combine butter and water in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil. Mix sugar and cornstarch, adding just enough cold water to make a paste.
Add to boiling water mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until apples are done.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in
soy
sauce, lemon juice and garlic powder, 12 to 24 hours before dinner.

title: chicken pie
directions: Stew
chicken. Remove from bones and shred.
Mix with soups and broth from cooked chicken.
Put in casserole.
Top with biscuits which have been flattened. Bake at 375° until browned.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes. Salt to taste with popcorn salt while hot.
Cool to serve.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix 2 cups of flour with fruit, nuts and raisins.
Cream egg yolks with butter and sugar.
Add lemon extract.
Add remaining (3 cups) flour and soda water.
Mix thoroughly.
Add fruit and nuts mixture.
Don't worry if batter is dry.
Fold in beaten egg whites (last).
Batter is still quite dry.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.
If you make only half the recipe, bake only 1 3/4 hours.
Wrap in cloth moistened with rum or apple cider.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Chop onion, carrots and celery fine.
Crumble sausage and ground chuck together and brown.
Add onion, carrots and celery. Make a place in center of meat to put chopped garlic to allow to fry in grease.
Drain grease off meat.
Pour into slow cooker.
Add parsley, oregano, basil, bay leaf and tomato puree.
Add about 1/2 soup can of water.
Simmer 2 to 4 hours.

title: chicken and crumbs bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix garlic, basil, oregano and salt with bread crumbs.
Melt margarine and brush each chicken breast with it.
Roll each piece in bread crumb mixture.
Place them in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Mix wine and onions and pour over chicken.
Return chicken to oven for 3 to 5 minutes, or until sauce is hot.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: irish sherry trifle
directions: Put a layer of sponge cake, about 3/4 inch thick, at bottom of dish.
A clear glass dish (about 3-quart) is preferable.
Coat lightly with jam and saturate with half of sherry.
Arrange ladyfingers in standing position around dish.
Cover sponge cake with 1/2-inch layer of both gelatins.
Cover with layer of cool custard.
Repeat procedure 2 more times.
Place whipped cream on top and garnish with cherries or strawberries.
Chill and serve. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Soften dough and spread on a greased pizza pan.
Shape crust. I oil my hands to spread dough. Bake at 425° for 6 minutes.
Dough will spread!
Let cool.

title: chicken zucchini casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup together.
Layer baking dish with chicken pieces and zucchini on top.
Pour sour cream and soup mixture over zucchini.
Top with Stove Top bread crumbs and seasoning packet.
Pour melted margarine over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan and bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°. Crust will form on bottom, custard in middle and coconut on top.

title: chicken and cheese dish
directions: Lay chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese. On top of cheese, pour undiluted soup.
Cover with stuffing mix. Top with butter and bake until chicken is done in 325° oven.

title: nanny babe's candied dill pickles
directions: Drain, rinse and slice pickles into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand for 48 hours at room temperature.
Stir often.
Put back into jar and refrigerate.

title: mashed potato rolls
directions: Mix spuds, milk, shortening, sugar and salt;; bring to a boil and cool.
Mix warm water and yeast; add beaten eggs, flour and potato mixture.
Knead; let rise twice.
Make into rolls.
Note: Makes sticky dough.

title: sicilian cream cake
directions: Slice sponge cake layer (either bought or homemade) into 3 thin layers and sprinkle each with 2 tablespoons rum.
Mash cheese smooth with a fork and work in 1/2 cup of the powdered sugar gradually and smoothly.
Stir in chocolate, cherries and cinnamon into cheese mixture.
Spread over cake layers and stack layers on top of each other.
Add toasted almonds to cheese mix.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Wash, hull and mash 2 quarts strawberries.
Add 1 cup sugar; let stand 1 hour; strain.
Add juice or oranges and lemons, cold water and sugar.
Pour into large punch bowl.
Add 1 quart whole strawberries.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Preheat Crisco 1 1/2 minutes in saucepan.
Debone salmon.
Mix other ingredients.
Beat well until frothy.
Scoop out 1 teaspoon mixture; drop in hot grease.
Cook immediately.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well and blend with sugar and salt.
Beat mixture until well blended.
Add melted butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start baking in preheated 450° to 500° oven until top and crust begin to brown.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until tester comes out clean.

title: curry dip
directions: Stir all together for a good vegetable dip.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: *Fill cup rest of the way with water.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and crackers.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top, then dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt lu's biscuits
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix. Form into a ball (or a few smaller balls).
Put flour on waxed paper and flour on dough.
Roll out, cut and put in ungreased pan. Bake at 375° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: bar cookie
directions: Melt stick of oleo in a bowl and add cake mix along with other ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can vary recipe by changing flavors of cake mix and chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion
in
margarine
until clear.
Mix all other ingredients well
with onions.
Put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes, until filling is slightly firm, at 375°.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Beat 3 or 4 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour in deep tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham glaze
directions: Boil until thickens.
Cool and spread over sliced ham.

title: marilyn's spaghetti
directions: Bring water to a boil and cook spaghetti, uncovered, for 8 minutes.
Drain well in strainer.
In frying pan, brown ground beef on low-medium heat. Stir lightly.
In a small saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce over low heat.
When meat is ready, pour sauce over it and stir until mixed well.
Place spaghetti in large dish and pour meat sauce over it.
Serve and enjoy!
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cook sliced onions in water to cover with 1/2 teaspoon salt for 20 minutes or until tender; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, remaining salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Fold in cheese and then onions.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: blueberry take-along cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cut in shortening until in very fine particles.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and thick.
Spread batter into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle berries over top.
Combine Streusel ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries.

title: you're lucky if you get a piece
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and frozen topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix lemon pudding with milk.
When pudding has set spread on cheese mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with Dream Whip if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and butter to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and drop by rounded tsp. onto waxed paper.

title: orange drink
directions: Blend smooth for 30 seconds.
Makes 3 cups.

title: toffee bars
directions: Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat with fork until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cut into squares or bars just a few minutes after removing from oven.
(If it cools, it's very difficult to cut.)
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if you like.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix spaghetti, Accent, Crisco oil and lemon juice and let stand 3 hours, then add green onion, olives, salad dressing and pimiento.

title: forgotten stew
directions: Pour tomato juice over everything.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 250° oven for 4 to 6 hours.
Do not peek.
This makes its own gravy.
Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Bake the chicken at 350° for about 45 minutes, turning once. Cut the chicken in 2-inch pieces.

title: spicy chicken appetizers
directions: Arrange chicken wings in a shallow baking dish.
Combine soy sauce, sugar, oil, mustard and wine.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over chicken wings.
Marinate for 4 hours or longer.
Bake in marinade at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, turning once and basting occasionally while cooking.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot or cold.

title: flan
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in the blender (safe).
In a square mold make the caramel with 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon water. Stir on medium-high until it is golden brown (safe).
Put the mix from the blender into the mold with the caramel.
Cover with foil paper and bake in a double boiler for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Chill for 1 or 2 hours.
Turn it over and enjoy.

title: "cathy and grandma's meat loaf"
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Make into 2 loaves.
Put on broiler pan with rack.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes.

title: homestyle zucchini fritters
directions: Wrap chopped zucchini in paper towels to dry.
Heat 2 or 3 inches of Crisco in deep fryer or heavy skillet.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and 2 teaspoons of melted shortening in medium bowl.
Stir in zucchini, add to flour mixture.
Mix just until moistened.
Drop by tablespoons into shortening.
Fry 3 or 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn as needed for even browning.
Remove; and drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: old fashioned ice cream
directions: Mix in a 4 quart freezer.

title: stuffed cabbage and sauerkraut
directions: Soak the head of cabbage for 10 minutes in boiling water. Drain and carefully separate leaves removing all hard core.
Mix together the ground beef and pork with egg, spices and chopped onion, bread crumbs and diced bacon.
Divide the mixture onto the cabbage leaves.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Arrange sauerkraut over bottom of pan.
Lay cabbage rolls on top. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Pour V-8 juice over top and simmer for 1 hour.
Before serving, stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly. Serve with rye bread.

title: sangria slush
directions: Combine juice concentrates and water.
Freeze in ice cube trays until firm.
To serve, add cubes to glasses; pour in wine and add fruit.
Makes 4 cups.
Must do ahead.

title: hamburg vegetable fry
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix together all ingredients and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place the chicken pieces in a single layer.
In a small bowl, combine the diced bread, eggs and milk.
Cover the chicken with the mixture, then cover the bread mixture with the corn bread stuffing mix.
In another bowl, combine the chicken broth and melted butter.
Stir to blend.
Pour over the corn bread stuffing mix.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with chicken gravy, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: inman chicken dish
directions: Mix all ingredients (except rice) together.
Put half of Rice-A-Roni on bottom of a large baking dish; add chicken mixture. Top with remaining Rice-A-Roni.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot kalaches
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add flour.
Shape dough into ball; chill overnight.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares; place 1/2 teaspoon apricot preserves in center.
Bring 2 sides together and pinch tightly.
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Place on cookie rack on waxed paper; sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot and again when cooled.

title: fruity breakfast bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In bowl, beat together honey, brown sugar, vanilla, oil and egg until well blended.
Fold in undrained pineapple, whole wheat flour, 1/4 cup oats, raisins and nuts.
Turn into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining oats.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until center is just firm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Yields 12 servings.

title: georgia apple cake
directions: Sift together twice flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix until a stiff dough forms.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown.
Serves 12 to 14.
Freezes well.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Shape into patties.
Roll in additional bread crumbs and brown lightly in butter over medium heat until hot through.
Serve on toasted English muffins with lettuce and mayonnaise.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish. Spread pie filling over oleo.
Mix cake mix and nuts until crumbly.
Spoon over the pie filling. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Turn heat up to 350° and brown 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear, stirring.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved and cool slightly.
Place fresh, sliced strawberries into baked shell and pour jello ingredients over berries; serve with whipped cream.
(You may use fresh raspberries with raspberry jello.)

title: chicken ole
directions: Grease sides and bottom of crock-pot.
Alternate layers of tortillas and chicken with mixture of undiluted soups, salsa, sour cream and onion.
Cover and cook on low for 4 or 5 hours. Sprinkle with cheese and cook on low for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: english toffee dessert
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add candy.
Stir well. Cool; mixture thickens as it cools.

title: meatball ratatouille
directions: Mix beef, milk, seasoning, onion powder, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/4 tsp. pepper, and garlic in a bowl.
Using a tablespoon, shape 1 1/4 inch meatballs; about 20.
In 2 batches, brown meatballs in oil in a large deep skillet for 4 minutes.
Remove to a paper towel lined plate.
Add eggplant, zucchini, red pepper, onions, remaining salt and black pepper to skillet; cook 3 minutes.
Add meatballs and tomatoes to skillet.
Cover; simmer 18 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Serve with noodles if desired.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
While hot, pour entire bottle of dressing over pasta.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: ranch burger
directions: Mix well and make 4 patties.
Grill or broil until done.

title: real lemonade
directions: Combine ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill, if desired.
Serve over ice.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: jeff's chicken pies
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, rosemary and pepper.
Add broth.
Stir to mix well.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cubed chicken, vegetables and pimento.
Beat until bubbly.
Pour mixture into cake pan.
Place biscuits onto top of mixture.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: beef lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in frypan; drain.
Add tomatoes, pizza sauce, salt, basil and oregano.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Reserve 1 cup of ground beef sauce for topping.
Place 1 cup of remaining meat sauce in bottom of a greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Top with half the noodles; cover with half the remaining meat sauce, 1/2 cup cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Repeat with remaining noodles.
Distribute reserved meat sauce over top; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes; let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt margarine, add other ingredients and spread on bread. Cut day old bread into sticks and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 2 hours at 200°.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Mix milk, butter and eggs well and spray crock-pot with nonstick spray. Put in macaroni. Mix in milk mixture and 2 cups of cheese. Put 1 cup of cheese on top. Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces. Combine ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer about 8 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain; do not chill.
While hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion, seasoning and cheese.
Toss well.
Gently mix in diced ham and remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on salad greens.

title: potato stuffed peppers
directions: Make mashed potatoes, but omit the milk.
Fry 1 small onion in butter and mix with potatoes.
Mix together Parmesan cheese and 2 beaten eggs.
Add to potatoes.
Add dash of garlic powder and parsley.
Stuff peppers with potato mixture and make a cork out of bread for the end of each pepper.
Place on an oiled roasting pan. Cover and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes on each side.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: garbage
directions: Combine cereal, raisins and peanuts.
Combine margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips and melt.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Mix and put in paper garbage bag or large Tupperware bowl.
Pour in powdered sugar and shake until coated.
Makes a great snack for a children's party or adult.
Or put in decorative containers and give as gifts.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.

title: southern creamed corn
directions: Cut corn off the cob; scrape well to remove corn milk.
Place cut corn in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add needed amount of water, sugar, butter and cornmeal; stir well.
Cover with plastic wrap or glass lid.
Microwave at High 2 minutes.
Stir well; rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes; stir well.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: macaroni and beef italiano
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and beef in salad oil.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups spaghetti sauce, 1 teaspoon salt,
basil
and water. Bring to a boil, cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
In
a
saucepan, melt butter, add flour and gradually blend in
milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add
cheese,
teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Stir	until
cheese melts.
Pour meat sauce into a 3 quart greased casserole dish or
x
9 x 2-inch pan. Spoon macaroni on top.
Smother with cheese sauce. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Drizzle
remaining
sauce on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: shredded yams
directions: Peel and shred potatoes.
Soak for several minutes in mixture of 1 gallon water and salt.
Drain and rinse.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour pineapple juice over potatoes.
Mix sugar, syrup and 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in margarine.
Add to potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: oreo stuff
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart dish, crumble Oreos to cover the bottom of the container.
Prepare pudding according to box directions and cover cookies.
Cover pudding with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cookie crumbs over top of dessert.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco mix, onion, green pepper, tomato sauce, dry mustard and beans.
Put in baking dish.
Combine sour cream and chili powder; spread on top of meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese has thoroughly melted.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Pet milk together and bring to boil. After ingredients have come to a boil let cook 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Add marshmallows until melted.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well and drop from teaspoon on wax paper and let cool.
(Mixture should be in cookie form when cool.)

title: hot dog treats
directions: Cut dogs into threes.
Wrap bacon around each hot dogs having toothpick hold in position.
Layer dogs and bacon on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Decorate with cherries.
Great to make up ahead of time for special occasions.

title: mud(serves 6)
directions: Finely crush 6 whole graham crackers in a large ziploc bag. Put chocolate pudding and 3 cups of milk into a jar.
Shake for 2 minutes and poor into 6 small mugs or cups.
Sprinkle crushed graham crackers over pudding.
Dig holes for the "seeds" and stick in a gummi worm.

title: christmas dessert
directions: Melt butter and oil.
Fold in marshmallows.
When ingredients are melted, pour in peanuts and M&M's.
Pour over popcorn and press into an angel food cake pan.
Let cool.
Turn out on a plate.

title: snowball cake(make this the night before.)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water, lemon juice, orange juice, sugar and salt.
Mix and refrigerate.
Bake angel food cake.
Remove cake from pan when cool.
Remove brown crumbs and break cake into small pieces.

title: italian pizza loaf(looks very fancy, very little work!)
directions: In a medium skillet, saute beef until browned; drain fat.
Mix in tomato sauce, onion and mushrooms.
Add paprika, oregano and garlic salt.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in olives, green pepper and Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, place onions, green pepper, chicken broth, tomato liquid, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, Kellogg's All-Bran cereal and turkey sausage. Cover pan and cook over medium heat until mixture starts to boil. Stir in chicken.
Lower heat and simmer 25 minutes or until moisture is absorbed and rice is cooked.
Remove bay leaf and stir in parsley.
Serve hot.
Makes 9 cups.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Spoon into a small ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers or sourdough or French bread cubes.

title: texas hash browns
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with 1 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes or cracker crumbs, mixed with 1 stick oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(A little longer if using raw potatoes.)
Cover with aluminum foil before baking.

title: roasted tomato salsa
directions: Place whole tomatoes into a small, shallow pan.
Broil under medium heat.
Turn tomatoes on all sides until skin is blistered and burnt, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Place tomatoes in blender or food processor fitted with the metal blade.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
May be stored in the refrigerator for several months.
Makes 1 cup.
Serve with corn chips or on lightly toasted baguette bread.

title: stir-fried pork chops and broccoli with oyster sauce
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets and small pieces.
Partially cook stem pieces in microwave.
Remove excess fat from pork chops. Make some cuts on the edge of the pork chops and pound the meat slightly.
Heat wok or large frying pan with oil.
Add pork chops and cook until almost done, about 5 minutes.
Remove the pork chops and cut them into thin slices.
Stir-fry the broccoli and mushrooms until almost done.
Add the sliced pork chops and finish cooking.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add oyster sauce. Stir well.
Remove from wok and serve.

title: crispy parmesan chicken tenders
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Combine crumbs, cheese, parsley and garlic salt.
Whisk egg whites and water.
Dip chicken into egg mixture and coat evenly with crumb mixture.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with ranch dressing.
Can use honey mustard if desired.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and cheese together. Blend in flour, salt and paprika.
Knead with hands to form a soft dough.
Form small balls with mixture and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press balls down slightly.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: kahlua
directions: In heavy Dutch kettle, bring water, sugar and coffee to boil. Simmer 1 hour and cool.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Cheers.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add milk, eggs and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add the next 5 ingredients to ground beef.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Set aside.
To ground beef mixture, add remaining ingredients.
Combine ingredients and cook over medium heat until completely blended.
In large buttered baking dish, layer noodles, meat mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Top with sharp Cheddar and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tator tot casserolelubbock, texas
directions: Brown ground meat and pour off grease until dry.
tags: cream of mushroom soup/cream of chicken

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the butter with the brown sugar.
Add the egg yolk and mix well.
Add the flour, vanilla and maple flavoring.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Quickly spread chocolate bits on top while hot.
Sprinkle with nuts or nuts, cinnamon and sugar.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook a chicken until tender.
Save the broth and cut the meat into small pieces.
In butter, saute until soft the green pepper, onion and celery.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender in 1 1/2 quarts boiling water to which 1 1/2 teaspoons salt has been added.
Lightly brown the onion in margarine.
Add the ground beef; cook slowly until brown. This will take about 10 minutes.
Blend in the flour.
Add Veg-All, including the liquid.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Pour into greased baking dish; bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: melting dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Chop 1/2 cup dried apricots; set remainder aside for decoration.
In medium size bowl, combine chopped apricots, coconut, flour and grated orange peel; toss to mix well.
Set aside.
In large bowl, using wire whisk or fork, beat eggs, baking mix, milk, melted butter, granulated sugar and vanilla extract until thoroughly blended. Stir in apricot-coconut mixture.
Pour mixture into prepared pie plate.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Cook until done. Then mash until smooth. Add butter. Mix in well. Then add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Then put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and serve. You can also freeze. Garnish with parsley to serve.

title: cream filled oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all but dry oatmeal.
Blend for 2 minutes. Fold in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Bake at 375°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
Pair by size.

title: wassail
directions: Boil water; turn off burner and add tea bags, cinnamon sticks and cloves and let sit for 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add pineapple juice, lemonade concentrate (with 3 cans of water) and orange concentrate (with 3 cans of water) along with the sugar and stir.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Must be refrigerated when not being served.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
In a medium saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over hot cake; cool completely.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Spread pudding over pineapple. Slice bananas over top of the pudding.
Spread whipped topping over bananas.
Keep cake refrigerated.
Serves 12.

title: oriental hot munch
directions: Preheat skillet, uncovered, at 225° with butter, soy sauce, seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly to blend. Heat 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve warm. Makes 3 quarts.

title: hot pineapple
directions: Put pineapple in 9-inch round or square baking dish.
Mix with cheese.
Mix together juice, flour and sugar and pour over pineapple.
Spread Ritz crackers over top. Melt 1 cube of oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered).

title: cry babies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, molasses, flour, ginger and salt.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Boil the water and add the soda.
Then add to flour mixture.
May add 1 cup raisins and 1/2 cup nuts to dough.
Drop by spoon to cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: russian rock cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. When well-creamed, add eggs, molasses, chopped nuts and raisins. Scrape down bowl and add flour.
(This mixture should be moist enough to stay together, but not dry enough to work by hand).

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients and place in freezer to freeze.

title: rutabaga soup
directions: Dice ham, rutabaga, potatoes and onions; put in 4 quart kettle and cook until tender.
Add peas and carrots and parsley and dried celery flakes (make thickening for soup).
Heat skillet; add vegetable oil, flour and salt and turn heat to medium; let flour brown (do not burn), stirring frequently.
When brown, add water. Let thicken to medium thick; pour into soup and stir.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix together.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Spread each ingredient evenly over pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top lightly browns.

title: strawberry yogurt
directions: Combine yogurt, milk powder, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in fruit.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased large casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple orange frost
directions: Blend pineapple and ice cubes at low speed until ice melts. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend 30 seconds at high speed.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with milk in heavy saucepan or double boiler. Stir in pecan pieces.
Drop by teaspoonful on buttered formica surface; let cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions together.
Drain and pour in casserole dish.
Add soy sauce to soup and pour beef.
Spoon peas over soup, then Tater Tots.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Halve zucchini, scoop out center, leaving 1/4-inch edge. Place in baking dish.
Take center you have scooped out; chop and mix with all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan.
Add Cheddar cheese and spoon into zucchini shells. Top with spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well and shape into balls.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Drain mushrooms. Saute first 5 ingredients in skillet until beef is brown and onion tender.
Drain.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Soften bread with the milk.
Juice from the pineapple can be used, adding milk to make a cup.
Combine remaining ingredients. Bake in deep casserole for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Grease and flour 1 round pan. Pour half the batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt the caramels, milk and oleo.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over it.
Pour remaining batter on top. Return to oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes more.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: heavenly coconut cake
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into an 11 x 15-inch baking pan, greased and floured, or 2 small layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Frost while still warm.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Mix
well and pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown. This pie makes its own crust.
Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Steam broccoli slightly without salt.
Place in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Drain tuna; put on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, milk and cheese in saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over tuna and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry jell salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water, then add 1 cup of cold water and the can of cherry pie filling.
Let set in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add applesauce alternately with dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add raisins and nuts; blend well.
Bake in well-greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: apple pudding sauce
directions: In baking dish, layer sides and bottom with vanilla wafers, then one layer of apple sauce and one layer vanilla wafers until dish is full.
Pour pudding mix in dish, over cookies and applesauce.
Take a fork, loosen up and let the mixture go through. Beat egg white until fluffy and place on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown (it browns fast).

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mix with other ingredients.
Let marinate a day or so.
This will keep indefinitely.
It is rather tart.

title: jackie's cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend ingredients with electric mixer. Refrigerate until firm.
Divide and form into three balls.
Roll in chopped nuts or parsley.
To use as a dip, add more vinegar.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease and flour loaf pan.
In small bowl, stir flour, baking powder and salt to mix well; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy; beat eggs, orange juice and orange peel in thoroughly.
Reduce speed to low; beat in flour mixture just until blended.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Spoon into prepared pan; bake 30 to 40 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.

title: grandma's teacakes
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time. Add flour to egg mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Add vanilla. Cover and chill 1 hour. Roll into 1/4-inch thickness and cut out. Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Soak yeast in 1/4 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar and salt; stir to dissolve.
Beat in butter, eggs and 1 cup flour (not sifted) until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until dough is no longer sticky. Place in greased bowl; grease top of dough and cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Work down and form into rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet; let rise until doubled in size.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date-coconut confections
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grind walnuts and dates in food chopper or chop very fine by hand.
Add sugar, 1 cup of coconut and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into remaining coconut. Shape into balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: grandpa's easy apple cobbler
directions: Sprinkle apples with a small amount of sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder, egg, sugar and salt until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Throw together, mix and pour onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to moderate or 375°.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift together the flour and 3/4 cup of sugar four times.
Place egg whites and salt in large bowl of electric mixer. Move bowl control so beater nearly touches side of bowl all during beating; move bowl control back and forth frequently.
Beat at speed 7 to a coarse foam, about 30 seconds.
Sprinkle cream of tartar and extract over surface of egg whites.
Beat at speed 7 for 1 minute, until whites slightly peak and are very moist and slightly foamy.
Beating at speed 7, add 1 cup of sugar in 2 tablespoon portions, and beat until mixture holds peaks, but tip of peak falls over, about 1 1/4 minutes.
Stop mixer; scrape sides of bowl and beater.
Fold at speed 1 for 1/2 minute.
Pour batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, invert and allow to cool completely before removing from pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Beat eggs and cheese together.
Add cornbread mix, margarine, onion and broccoli. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes until lightly brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix cooked chicken, Veg-All and soup together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place one pie crust on bottom of pie plate. Pour chicken mixture over pie crust.
Put 2nd pie crust on top. Pinch together pie crust on sides.
Poke with fork (4 times). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 10 ingredient salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except sliced hard-boiled eggs. Sprinkle sugar and hard-boiled egg slices on top.
Let sit 24 hours in refrigerator and serve.

title: christmas pizza
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat until smooth, using food processor or electric mixer.
Spread evenly on a 12-inch plate (pizza plate).
Spread chili
sauce evenly over cheese, leaving 3/4-inch margin.
Sprinkle crabmeat over chili sauce.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: apple or rhubarb squares
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oil and vanilla.
Fold in apples or rhubarb.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
(These freeze well.)

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Pie makes its own pie crust.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite zucchini nut bread
directions: With a mixer, beat the eggs.
Add sugar, oil and zucchini. Sift the dry ingredients and add.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pans and cool.
These freeze well.

title: apricot filling
directions: Cook all ingredients until softened. Blend in blender until smooth. Add vanilla and cinnamon. Mix well.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Beat ingredients 2 minutes at high speed.
Place cones in muffin pan and fill 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and ice with icing.
Makes 36.
Enjoy!

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat until fluffy.

title: low cholesterol marinade for fish
directions: Combine the wine, corn oil, garlic powder, parsley, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over fish in oven pan.
Top with the olives, mushrooms and pimientos.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake fish at 350° for 45 minutes, less if thin pieces, or until fish flakes with fork.

title: buttered browned potatoes
directions: Peel baking potatoes.
Cut each to 6 slices.
Dry.
Coat in 1/4 cup melted butter in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, in a single layer, for 20 minutes. Uncover, baste with other 1/4 cup of butter and bake 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: old fashion macaroni cheese
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour to make a paste.
Add salt and milk stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat. Add cheese.
Pour over cooked macaroni in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy eggless raisinful cake
directions: In a two-quart saucepan, boil raisins in water for ten minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, stirring to melt.
Add molasses, followed by all unsifted dry ingredients.
Mix to blend well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Decorate with a white frosting for dessert. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar for a snack, or leave plain for breakfast.

title: mathis' family chicken stew
directions: Begin with a 10 to 12 gallon black iron pot with lid.
Add 1/2 gallon of water to pot.
Place cooked and deboned chicken plus broth into pot.
Heat to boiling.
Remove heat from under pot and let mixture cool.
Add butter, salt, black and red pepper and milk. Mix well.
Prepare thickening by measuring 1 pint flour and placing in quart jar.
Add enough water to fill jar.
Attach lid and shake vigorously until all flour is dissolved and there are no lumps. Add thickening mixture to cooled stew.
Mix well and reheat stew until it just begins to boil.
Remove from heat and enjoy.
Serves 50 to 75.

title: kentucky-fried corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon grease; stir to blend. Melt grease in a large frying pan.
Add corn mixture and simmer on low heat for about 40 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Cook (except vanilla) until 243°.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Pour into well-greased glass (if possible) dish to cool. Cut in pieces and wrap individually.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all of ingredients together (except pretzels).
Place pretzels in bowl or long dish.
Pour rest of ingredients over pretzels and mix well.
Microwave for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave for 2 minutes more.

title: tortilla roll-up appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and green onions.
Spread on tortillas, then remaining ingredients.
Roll each tortilla tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut into slices.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large skillet, combine milk, sugar and margarine.
Stir on medium heat.
Do not allow to come to boil until all sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boiling and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla; stir until marshmallows have melted and mixture is well blended.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: all-purpose meat sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of oil until soft. Brown ground beef, breaking up fine as it cooks.
Mix the spaghetti sauce mix according to directions and add 1 cup to meat mixture, saving remainder in freezer until next time!
Add remainder of ingredients, mixing well, and simmer, covered, for several hours, stirring frequently.
If sauce gets too thick, add a little hot water or more tomato sauce. When using as spaghetti sauce, serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: microwave chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts between wax paper and beat with meat mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Melt margarine in small bowl in microwave for 45 seconds.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, paprika and tarragon in a separate bowl and set aside.
Place cheese and ham on top of chicken breasts and roll up, securing chicken with wooden toothpick.
Dip in margarine and roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken breasts, seam side down, in 2-quart baking dish. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes on High, turning dish half turn after first 4 minutes.

title: strawberry pineapple cooler
directions: In blender container, combine strawberries and pineapple; blend until smooth.
In pitcher, combine strawberry puree, pineapple juice and cream of coconut.
Just before serving, add club soda. Scoop sherbet into glasses; pour in juice mixture.

title: beef 'n ale
directions: Mix beef, dry soup mix, ginger ale and cream of mushroom soup together.
Bake in Dutch oven or large covered casserole dish at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or until beef is very tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans; set aside.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Make cornbread according to package directions.
Let cool (overnight if possible).
Crumble cornbread and toast into large mixing bowl.
Add onion, celery and poultry seasoning.
Mix well. Add hot broth until mixture is a very mushy consistency.
Stir in eggs, salt and pepper.
Transfer to a large roasting pan and cook at 350° until firm and browned on top.
Serves a large group.

title: tuna salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
When cool, beat mixture until frothy.
Fold in mayonnaise, celery, nuts, tuna, chopped eggs and onion.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into glass dish.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with sliced black olives on top.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine broccoli, egg, mayonnaise, and cream of mushroom soup.
Put into a baking dish sprayed with Pam and top with the cheese and then the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Note: If the recipe is doubled, add 15 minutes to the baking time and use three (3) pkgs. of frozen broccoli.

title: ginger steamed fish
directions: Wash the fish under cold running water.
Pat dry.
Rub a little flour onto fish skin surfaces.

title: broccoli-cheddar strata
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cube bread.
Grate Cheddar cheese. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
In casserole, evenly layer broccoli, bread, 1/2 of the cheese and onion.

Evenly sprinkle remainder of cheese on top. Whisk remaining ingredients and pour over top of the casserole. Bake for 40 minutes or until custard is slightly puffed and let cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is no longer pink.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Drain all but 2 to 3 Tbsp. of drippings.
Cook onions until tender.
Stir in flour; blend well.
Add vinegar and water, cook and stir until bubbly and slightly thick.
Add sugar and stir until it dissolves.
Crumble bacon.
Gently stir in bacon and pototoes.
Heat thoroughly, stirring lightly to coat potato slices.
Serve warm.

title: savory italian beef
directions: Brown roast in hot skillet.
Place roast in crock-pot. Sprinkle dressing and soup mixes over meat.
Pour beer or broth over meat.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Remove meat from cooker and shred.
If thicker gravy is desired, stir cornstarch into water until all lumps are gone.
Return shredded meat to pot. Cover and cook on high another 15 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole, ungreased, and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream bananas to liquid state.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Chop pecans.
Blend margarine with sugar.
Beat in 2 eggs and blend well.
Add flour mixture and mix well until no flour appears.
Add bananas and blend.
Add pecans and mix well.
Turn into a greased tube pan.
Cook in a 350° oven 35 to 45 minutes (or until cake tester comes out clean).

title: tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold water to soften.
Add to boiling
V-8 juice; cool.
When cool, add celery.
Pour into mold or individual molds and refrigerate until stiff.

title: bonnie's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
both
the
rice
and
the
broccoli
according to package directions.
Combine the cooked rice and broccoli with the Cheez Whiz, butter, water chestnuts, soup and pimento; mix well. Pour
into
a
3-quart (or 2 smaller) greased casserole dish. Bake
at
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and cover the
top with
grated cheese.
Place back into the oven until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate snake
directions: Combine peanut butter and dry milk powder in mixing bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Stir in, one at a time, honey, cocoa, vanilla, nuts, raisins, dates and coconut.
Clean hands work well for this.
Put mixture on waxed paper and roll into the shape of a fat snake.
Pull or cut off pieces; they're ready to eat.
Wrap snake in wax paper and store in refrigerator.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Layer crust and peaches, ending with crust.
Bake in oven at 350° until browned.

title: coconut nut frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on baked cake.
Put under broiler until bubbly and light brown.

title: pineapple cake with icing
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add water and chicken bouillon; bring to a boil.
Add fine egg noodles.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook 4 minutes.
Add milk and cheese. Bring to a boil and simmer.
Add pepper to taste.

title: 5 pound fudge candy
directions: Combine the milk and sugar in a heavy saucepan and boil for 4 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into a greased pan and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: chow mein
directions: Bring all ingredients, except chow mein noodles, to a boil, stirring all the time. Put in casserole dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° for 15 minutes before you take it out of the oven. Add chow mein noodles.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil and pineapple with juice.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and blend.
Don't beat.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a tube pan.
Let cool before removing.

title: breakfast in a glass
directions: Put all except ice cubes into blender.
Cover.
Process at "liquify".
With motor running, remove feeder cap.
Add cubes one at a time.
Continue to process until smooth.
Makes 2 servings, 285 calories each serving.

title: dessert sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter and jelly on bread.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Shake on colored sprinkles.
Add a layer of mini marshmallows.
Put cover bread on top to make sandwich.
Enjoy your dessert while you eat your sandwich.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown zucchini and onion in skillet.
Put in baking dish.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and pats of butter.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: yummies
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While hot, spread with chocolate chips and nuts.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake for 15 minutes and reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Continue baking for 35 or 40 minutes, or until knife inserted near the edge comes out clean.

title: jennifer's fruit cookies
directions: Fruits should be cut.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes 14 dozen cookies.

title: marshmallow cookies
directions: Stir and drop on waxed paper.

title: teresa's tortilla soup
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Heat onion and pepper in skillet with 1 teaspoon butter for a few minutes.
Put all ingredients in a large stock pot.
Add 1 gallon of water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over crushed tortilla chips.
Top with 1 tablespoon grated cheese and sour cream.

title: b and c casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower over low heat until it thaws.
Drain and mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain fat. Add tomatoes, corn, green pepper and taco seasoning. Cook over medium heat until boiling. Spoon into 4 bowls. Top
with shells and cheese.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Split chicken into halves.
Mix together all ingredients except chicken, in a large pot over low heat.
When butter is no longer lumpy and sauce is hot, it's ready to use.
Apply to chicken every 5 to 10 minutes until chicken is completely done, 1 to 2 hours. Best barbecued over a charcoal pit.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix dough
in the evening.
Bake the next day in a 350° oven.

title: frozen heavenly fruit salad
directions: Blend sour cream, lemon juice and sugar.
Fold in bananas, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Spoon into a 7 x 3-inch loaf pan. Freeze until firm.
Garnish with cherries if desired.

title: beef curry
directions: I use this recipe for leftover beef and gravy.
Brown onion and green pepper.
Add gravy and curry powder.
(This will spice up the gravy; add until desired spiciness.)
Add beef (cubed), apples (cut in small pieces) and raisins.
Cook until apples are soft and raisins are plump.
Serve over rice.

title: hobo dinners
directions: Pat hamburger into 6 patties.
Place each on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Slice potato on each.
Slice carrot on each. Slice onion on each.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pat butter on each.
Roll up in foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir margarine, flour, bouillon cubes and milk until thick. Pour over broccoli.
Mix stuffing mix according to directions. Sprinkle on top.
Add nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shoestring apple pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie plates. Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until apples are soft.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and milk; beat until light and fluffy.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
On a lightly floured surface, roll 1/2 of the dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly, then remove from sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: apple mallow yam yums
directions: Toss apples and nuts combined with brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layer of apples and yams into 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows over yams and apple.
Return to oven.
Remove when light brown.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Dice bell pepper and onions.
Mix corned beef, cottage cheese, horseradish, bell pepper and onions.
Form into a ball and refrigerate for approximately 1 hour.
Coat with cream cheese. Serve with crackers.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix together in a ball.
May roll in diced nuts.
Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: margi's whiskey cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and oil; beat well after each.
Add cake mix and coconut pudding.
Mix and beat well.
Add chopped nuts to batter by hand.
Place cherries, cut side down in a greased and floured tube pan.
Pour batter over cherries.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream, brandy, vanilla and lemon and almond extracts; mix until well blended.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing until well blended.
Scrape batter into a well-buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted in thickest part comes out clean, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Set pan on a rack for about 10 minuets.
At top of pan, run a knife between cake and rim.
Invert onto rack; cool. Serves 16 to 18.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
(This should take about 2 months.)
Cover with brown gravy and cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 465°.
This serves 3,800.
If more servings are needed, add 2 rabbits.
Do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to fine hare in their stew!

title: pan-fried onion dip
directions: Cut the onions in half, then slice them about 1/8-inch thick half rounds (you should have about 3 cups of onions). Heat the butter and oil in a large saute pan on medium heat. Add onions, cayenne, salt and pepper and saute for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, stirring occasionally, for 20 more minutes, until onions are browned and caramelized. Allow onions to cool. Place cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise in a bowl; use an electric mixer and beat until smooth. Add onions and mix well. Serve at room temperature.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Have butcher run flank steak through tenderizer or cube steak machine once.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown squash, onion and oregano in margarine.
Add chopped tomatoes, corn, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into bowl; cut in shortening until dough resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend in molasses, eggs and milk.
Dough should resemble biscuit dough.
Roll or knead dough and pat into thin layers.
This makes 7 layers.
Bake in 9-inch pans, greased and lined with brown paper.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Turn out on cloth to cool.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Cook onions and 1/2 c. chopped celery in oil or oleo in heavy pot, uncovered.
Season to taste with salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper.
Cook slowly until onions are wilted.
Grind up boiled shrimp and crabmeat in food chopper.
Mix with onion mixture and cook 15 minutes over medium heat
uncovered.
Add buns which have been soaked in eggs; mix well.
Add bell pepper, remainder of celery, green onion tops, parsley and bread crumbs; mix well.
Split each fresh large shrimp lengthwise almost to the end and flatten out.
Stuff centers of split shrimp with mixture, holding each shrimp in the hand and squeezing it together to form a croquette.
Roll in flour, then in batter.
Fry quickly for 5 minutes in deep hot fat (375°).
Drain.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberries and stir until unjelled.
Stir in sour cream and pecans.
Pour into mold and let chill until firm.
Unmold and serve.

title: fat-free potato soup
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in pan.
Cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add can of skimmed milk.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in casserole in order listed.
Top with seasoned salt and pepper.
Pour soup over all and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and other ingredients.
Simmer 90 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak italian style
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs.
Then roll into 6 to 8 balls, then drop one ball into bread crumbs.
Cover well with fork, then in frying pan.
Add cooking oil.
Flatten balls with fork, then dry until done.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Prepare fruit:
crush 2 quarts of raspberries (should equal 4 cups of crushed berries).
Measure 4 cups into a large pot, stir sugar into the fruit,
mix thoroughly.
Add butter (reduces foaming).
Bring mixture full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Open Certo pectin pouch and quickly stir contents into fruit mixture.
Bring to full rolling boil again and continue boiling for one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off any foam with a large metal spoon.
Make sure you have jars ready and fill to 1/3 of inch from the top.
Wipe jar rims and threads and cover quickly with lids.
Screw bands on tightly.
Invert jars for 5 minutes then turn upright. Check lids to see if there is a slight bulging on top.
If there is, they are sealed.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In microwave, melt chocolate chips (or favorite chips), milk and
butter;
stir	occasionally,
for
about
minutes (depending	on
your
microwave).
When
melted,
remove
from microwave and add nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
(Butter is best to use to grease pan.) Place in refrigerator to cool.
Cut in squares when cooled.

title: pasta with chicken and sun dried tomatoes
directions: Heat oil.
Add chicken and saute until cooked, about 6 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Add to same oil the onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Add sun dried tomatoes and chicken and continue cooking about 2 minutes.
Transfer to bowl with chicken.
Add pasta and cheese; mix well.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups (do not dilute) and spices.
Heat and take out 1 cup of mixture (for reserve).
Add instant rice to remaining mixture; bring to a boil.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Place pieces of chicken breast on top and spread reserved cup of soup over top. Bake at 300° for about two hours (or microwave chicken until almost done, then add to above for shorter cooking time).

title: fresh veggie dip
directions: Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Use celery, carrots, cauliflower, cucumbers, radishes and other fresh vegetables to dip.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs and milk.
Blend in flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in raisins, nuts and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed on mixer.
Blend in cooled chocolate, then add flour, soda and salt mixture alternately with ice water.
Beat well after each addition.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: betty lou's sheet cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients and cream together.
In greased jelly roll pan, spread 2/3 of mixture and spread a can of fruit pie filling over batter and top with remaining 1/3 of batter.
Any canned or thawed frozen fruit may be used by thickening juice with cornstarch before spreading on batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: good chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chocolate morsels.
Pour into Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly, cut potatoes in half and scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour stirring constantly until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add 6 cups of milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add potato pulp and other ingredients except sour cream.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Blend together softened butter and filling.
Package in small plastic tub container.
Delicious!

title: rainbow salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in 1 cup	hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Cool.
When
slightly
thickened, fold in pineapple. Chill.
Dissolve lemon
gelatin in 1 1/2 cups hot water. Cool until slightly
thickened.	Whip
cream
and cream cheese and add to cool
lemon
gelatin.
Pour
mixture over firm lime gelatin mixture.
Let set.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Mix well.
In a separate small bowl, mix cocoa and red food coloring, making a paste.
Add vinegar to paste and mix well.
Add mixture to first batter, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Add salt and mix well.
Pour batter into greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: quick baked pasta, family style
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Brown beef with oil and garlic; drain.
Add all ingredients to beef except pasta and Mozzarella (or Swiss) cheese.
Simmer while pasta cooks. Drain pasta.
Mix in with sauce.
Spread baking dish with vegetable spray.
Pour mixture into dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: indian corn(stove top)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add corn and taco sauce.
Simmer mixture for 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german potato salad
directions: To potatoes, add the oil and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and serve warm or cold.

title: dirt
directions: Fix pudding according to directions on box.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding and let stand for 5 minutes.
Place half of cookie crumbs in a container.
Place Cool Whip mixture on top of cookie crumbs, then top with cookie crumbs.

title: carrot-cheddar casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl, reserving 1/4 cup crushed crackers.
Mix well.
Turn into greased casserole. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean at 350°.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix
well.
Knead 5 minutes on a floured board.
Let rise in a greased bowl for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut dough in half and roll into
x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread each half with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Combine
cup sugar with 1 tablespoon
cinnamon. Sprinkle
half
over each rectangle and roll lengthwise.
Slice each rectangle into 12 slices.

title: nachos
directions: Fry lean ground; add taco seasoning with 3/4 cup water. Place Tostitos
on
cookie sheet; layer other ingredients on. Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: white castle appetizers
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine all ingredients together.
Cut rolls in half (complete package).
Spread mixture on bottom half. Leave it in foil container.
Put pickle on top of each bun and return top portion of bun.
Wrap it all in foil.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 minutes, until hot.

title: sauerkraut in crock
directions: I use my Hamilton Beach chopper-slicer to chop the cabbage. Mix cabbage and salt well and stomp into crock until it draws water.
Repeat until crock is full.
Put water in large plastic bag and completely cover cabbage.
No waste.
Done when it has soured enough.
Cold pack in cans 20 minutes in hot water bath. Cover with juice or brine.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Combine drained kraut, celery, green pepper, onion and drained chopped pimento.
Mix with vinegar mixture.
Chill.

title: scalloped apples(side dish)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Stir well into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skinny dip
directions: Combine ingredients in blender. Cover and chill. Serve with veggies.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers in salt solution of 1/3 cup salt to each quart of water.
Let stand 12 hours (overnight).
Drain and dry. Combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Boil 10 minutes or until clear. Add cucumbers and let stand at low heat until they lose the green color and turn yellowish.
Put 1/2 teaspoon per pint jar (1 teaspoon per quart jar) of pickling spice in bottom of jar.
Add cucumbers.
Cover with the hot syrup and seal jars.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and flavorings and mix well.
Stir slowly into beaten eggs.
Pour into shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: karo winter casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in oil; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Add half of the cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: apple yam casserole
directions: Put yams in buttered 2 quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over yams.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
