title: rosamarina salad
directions: Prepare this the day before you intend to serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with a little milk.
Stir in spices.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Do not stir hard or fast or it will separate. Chill 24 hours.
Serve with vegetables.

title: ankuri cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour and vanilla. Mix and spread on a 14 x 10 5/8-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips on top of dough.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and then cut in squares.

title: chicken and sauerkraut
directions: Mix sauerkraut, tomato sauce and molasses.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add cut up chicken.
Cook bacon and sausage briefly.
Mix all together and simmer 1 hour.
Top with sour cream.

title: holiday salad
directions: Layer frozen peas, crumbled cooked bacon, chopped red onion, cheese and mayonnaise. Repeat three times and top with balance of cheddar cheese. Refrigerate till time to eat.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Fry tortillas in hot fat until they bubble.
Place in casserole.
Alternate a tortilla with onions and cheese until all are used up.
Mix together milk, green chilies and soup.
Heat. Pour mixture over top and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Combine oil and flour in skillet and make a dark roux or gravy. Add onions, celery, green peppers, garlic and okra (if using), plus onion tops. Cook until vegetables are soft and add seasonings and tomatoes. Add water and shrimp (may be cut in half). Cook about 1/2 hour or until shrimp are done. Serve over rice.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Spread batter in 2 greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: poppycock
directions: Pop the popcorn and set aside.
Melt butter; stir in syrup, sugar and salt.
Boil slowly, about 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn. Mix until popcorn is well coated.
Stir in 1 cup of mixed nuts or salted peanuts if desired.
Place on cookie sheets and bake in oven at 250° for 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally.
When done, spread out on waxed paper and cool.
Then break up into pieces.

title: chicken stew
directions: Brown chicken in Teflon frypan.
Add vegetables and saute until tender.
Remove chicken from pan and sprinkle whole wheat flour over vegetables until browned and very fragrant.
Add apple juice and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer until tender.
I add 3/4 of a cup of brown rice-----Delish!

title: shuttebutt
directions: Cook hash browns until completely cooked but not browned. Beat eggs; add other ingredients. Add to hash browns. Cook all together in skillet until eggs are done, stirring constantly. Serve with ketchup.

title: hot fudge sundae sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients except vanilla until thick.
Add vanilla. Serve over ice cream.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook and season to taste; drain.
In a buttered baking dish, combine beans, soup and 1/3 can onion rings.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle remaining onions over top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: chess pie cookies
directions: Melt oleo and add sugars.
Blend well.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to oleo, sugars and egg yolks.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Grease and flour a 9x
13-inch pan. Spread batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
When done, sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: frozen pistachio dessert
directions: Mix melted
butter
and cracker crumbs.
Press into pie plate like graham cracker
crust.
Combine ice cream, milk and pudding mix at slow
speed.
Spread
ice
cream
mixture
over crust and freeze.
Spread with Cool Whip or whipping cream and sprinkle with crumbs.
Freeze until
30 to 45 minutes prior to serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook onion and cabbage together and chop.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup with cabbage.
Place in casserole.
Top with stuffing and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients.
Put in loaf cake pan and set aside.
Melt the 3/4 cup oleo in saucepan and the 4 squares of chocolate.
Take off heat and add 3 cups powdered sugar and egg yolks (beaten).
Beat until well mixed.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Pour over crumbs and freeze. This mixture will not freeze hard.
Soften 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream and spread over top and freeze until firm.
Some crumbs may be kept for on top if desired.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: angel sweets
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Cool and beat in egg.
Stir in sugar, nuts and marshmallows.
Blend well. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate until needed.
Great for Christmas!!

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in beans, dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients and 1/2 cup cheese.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve with crisp tortillas if desired.
Add avocado last.

title: taco pie
directions: Crush Doritos chips for crust.
Brown slightly in pie pan. Brown meat; add seasoning.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Put this over crust.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple or berry pie filling
directions: Cook cornstarch and apple juice over medium heat, stirring with wire whip until thickened.
Add sugars and butter; stir.
Add spices.
Add sliced apples.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375° the first 15 minutes, then at 350° for the rest of the baking time.

title: grace murdoch's ham loaf
directions: Grind together ham and pork.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until thick stirring constantly. Pour over banana and vanilla wafers.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix the flour, shortening and sugar to crumbs.
In another bowl, combine the water, baking soda, Karo, molasses and egg.
Put half of the crumbs in liquid.
Mix. Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top. Bake in two 9-inch unbaked pie shells at 375°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with the grated cheese.
Crush the potato chips; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: cherry tart
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla slowly together.
Then add saltine cracker crumbs and nuts.
Spread on 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, then spread Dream Whip on top, then pie filling.

title: peter franck's black bean soup
directions: Pick over and wash beans.
Add water to cover and soak overnight or bring to a boil and let sit 1 hour; drain, rinse and add water to cover plus 1 bouillon cube or a teaspoon of salt. Cook until done, 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel and beat potatoes; mix with melted butter, sugar, eggs, milk, juice and grated rind of 1 orange. Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add coconut, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir well with spoon.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lois' sunday special
directions: Brown ground beef and onion or soup mix in skillet; drain off excess grease.
Spread in dish.
Mix soup in 1/2 cup of water. Pour on top of ground beef.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook potatoes according to directions.
Cook beef and onion in large skillet until beef is no longer pink.
Drain and add carrot.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Add broth; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened slightly. Spoon mixture into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Stir together the potatoes, eggs, remaining salt and pepper; spoon over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake five more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Garnish with parsley or dill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Bake the 2 pie crusts, then set aside. Mix everything together except the cheese. Pour into pie crusts. Sprinkle cheese over top. Put in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine sauteed onions with slightly beaten eggs.
Add undiluted soup, squash and cornbread.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and pour in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake ii
directions: In large bowl mix gelatin and sugar; add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
With electric mixer, beat in cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill until firm, at least 2 hours.
Top, if desired, with fresh fruit.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, oil and water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add pumpkin.
Add raisins and pecans.
Mix well.
Divide mixture in 3 bread pans.
Grease and flour bottom of pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: waldorf-astoria chocolate icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding powdered sugar.
Fold egg whites and sugar into chocolate mixture.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix and stir well and leave open 2 hours or so.
Then cover container to keep fresh.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk and mix with hands.
Pack in graham cracker box.
Tie and refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored.
Do not use mixer after this.
Stir in fruit cocktail with the juice, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Fill frying pan half full of cooking oil.
Place on medium-high heat.
Dip clean chicken in dry mixture and place in hot skillet. Fry until golden brown or when pierced, juices run clear.
Be sure not to overcook or chicken will become dry.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat margarine in a 3-quart pot until melted.
Add okra, onions and green pepper.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add broth, tomatoes, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add meat and parsley. Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat the 4 egg yolks; stir in the sweetened condensed milk and lime juice.
In a small bowl, beat one of the egg whites until it is stiff and fold it into the milk-lime mixture.
Turn into the pie shell.

title: cold peach soup
directions: Plunge peaches in boiling water for 1 minute. Drain, peel, halve and stone. Puree peaches in blender.
Transfer to saucepan and add wine, water, sugar, cinnamon and curry powder.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix warm mashed potatoes with sugar.
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll, then slice.
Refrigerate.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Fry celery, onions, cut-up potatoes, sage, salt and pepper. Simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Add broth as you are simmering.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sweetener, spice and salt.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat in pumpkin and vanilla.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: my favorite snack:  super apple combo
directions: Wash the apples and strawberries. Cut them in half two times. Then sprinkle cinnamon on them.
Put them in the pocket roll.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Stir cornstarch into 1/4 cup clam juice in cup and set aside. Add shrimp, garlic, red pepper and salt.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until shrimp begins to turn pink.
Remove shrimp.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Pour the scalded milk over the bread crumbs. Cool and add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° until silver knife inserted in pudding comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy creamed cabbage
directions: Add dressing to cabbage and pepper; toss and chill. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: rotel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave until cheese melts. Stir until smooth.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain.
Stir in beans, sauce, taco mix, 1/4 c. cheese.
Sprinkle 2-1/2 c. chips in bottom of 8 by 8 by 2 in. baking dish.
Cover with chili mix.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 min.
Spread sour cream over chili.
Top with chips and cheese, bake 3 min.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix 3 to 4 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, etc., to taste.
Then add sour cream and spaghetti sauce and stir well.
Pour noodles in bottom of large pan.
Then pour sauce mixture over noodles.
Then top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creole sauce
directions: Soften onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook until boiling.
Stir in cornstarch mixture, cooking just until thickened.
Serve over fluffy white rice.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Divide hamburger into 4 equal-size patties, placing each on a large square of heavy-duty tinfoil.
Place vegetables in equal amount on each patty.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap each patty in tinfoil and bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: southern hushpuppies
directions: Mix together cornmeal, self-rising flour, baking powder, salt and onion.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until creamy. (It should have the consistency of pancake mix.)
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease.

title: miss pearl's pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Sift ingredients together.
Add a small amount to creamed mixture.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well.
Add remaining flour alternately with milk. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cucumber salad(or tomato salad)
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers.
Core seeds.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix white vinegar with water.
Pour over sliced cucumbers (or tomatoes cut into thin wedges).
Toss.
Add vegetable oil; toss.
Add pinch of dill.
If desired, chopped Bermuda onion can be added.

title: polka daters
directions: Mix together dates and hot water.
Let this mixture cool.
In separate bowl, mix together the next three items.
Then sift together flour, baking soda and salt and stir in batter.
Add the next two ingredients, including date mixture.
Pour this batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, corned beef, dill weed, Beau Monde and onion.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, carve out the center of the bread to form a bowl.
Cut the portion of the bread removed from the center into 1-inch chunks to be used as "dippers".
Fill the bread bowl with the dip and arrange dippers around the bowl.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can Durkee French fried onions. Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cut onions in half and place in casserole.
Spread sauerkraut over onions.
Place ribs on top.
Brown in a 500° oven.
Reduce heat to 450°, cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 19 g, protein 20 g, fat 23 g, calories 351.

title: plum kuchen
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg.
Batter should be dry like cookie dough.
If too dry, add a little cream. Pat dough into bottom of layer cake pan.

title: linguine with garlicky clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine until just tender, but still firm to bite.
Melt butter with oil. Add garlic and cook until fragrant (1 minute). Add reserved clam juice, wine, carrot and oregano. Boil until reduced to 1 1/3 cups (about 12 minutes). Stir in clams and parsley.
Heat through and season with salt and pepper.
Drain linguine well.
Add to clam sauce. Toss to blend. Transfer to large platter and serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: german style cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Cook until tender.
Do not overcook.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake 30 minutes.

title: potato patch casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, egg, 1/4 cup milk, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Shape into 18 meatballs and brown in cooking oil. Make a white sauce with butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Combine potatoes, peas and carrots.
Place in roaster.
Arrange meatballs around edge of dish.
Cover with sauce.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In a medium microwave glass dish, put chocolate almond bark and white almond bark. Microwave for 3 minutes. Remove from microwave and stir to mix. Add peanuts or cashews. Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper. Yields 30 to 40 pieces.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, pour off grease.
Grease pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Take crescent rolls apart and stretch them as far as you can without tearing them.
Place side by side on pan. Take eggs and milk and mix together.
Pour part of this on crescent rolls, then alternate your sausage, cheese and eggs with cheese being your last topping.
Bake at 350° until eggs are done, knife will come out clean when inserted in center.
You can vary the toppings any way you like.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients, except Oreos; mix well.
For "dirt," grind Oreos in blender. Spread 1/2 of "dirt" in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread on cream mixture.
Put rest of "dirt" on top.
Chill 10 to 12 hours.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except cheese and Worcestershire sauce and spread in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Toss cheese and Worcestershire sauce and spread on top of the pie.
Bake 10 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 hearty servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of casserole dish.
Top with fried hamburger, chopped onion and taco seasoning, layering over beans.
Top with 1 large bag of shredded cheese.
Pour jar of salsa over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Line casserole dish with black olives and then spring onions.
Add chips around base of casserole for dipping.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease pie pan, then heap with apples.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Blend together the flour, sugar, margarine and egg.
Spread over apples.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm or cold.

title: curried scrod
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Place scrod in small casserole.
Pour mustard mixture over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Broil for 2 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water for 1 week.
Wash cucumbers and put back in jar.
Add alum.
Cover with scalding water and leave overnight.
Wash pickles again.
Heat one time the sugar, vinegar, spice and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 3 days, adding 1 cup sugar each day.
(These pickles do not have to be sealed.
I usually put a lid or tinfoil over mine.)

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Form into biscuits.
Lightly grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with butter and honey or butter and Cheddar cheese.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Slice bacon into 1/2-inch strips.
Saute bacon, onion and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain beans.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix jello and water.
Mix Mandarin oranges, orange juice and pineapple into Jell-O; chill to set in 9 x 13 pan.
Then top with Cool Whip and pudding mixture.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Put meat in crock-pot.	Chop garlic and place on top of meat. Chop onion and place on top of meat.
Pour tomatoes and green chilies
into crock-pot.
Slice tomatoes and chilies if desired. Add ground cumin.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high 5 to 6 hours.

title: fast and easy pancakes from scratch
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour onto hot griddle or pan.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Chop all peppers and onions fine (I use a food processor). Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain water.
Add sugar, salt and spices (put spices in a bag).
Add vinegar. Simmer 15 minutes.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Recipe requires no vinegar.

title: german chocolate pie(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo on low heat.
Let cool.
Add vanilla. In a small bowl, combine eggs, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg mixture. Add nuts and mix.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes until done.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken curry
directions: Combine ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie soup
directions: In saucepan, heat chicken broth, milk, thyme and bay leaves until simmering.
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in skillet, heat butter until melted.
Add chicken. Cook and stir until tender 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining butter; heat until melted.
Add mixed vegetables and sprinkle with flour. Stir until vegetables are coated.
Add to milk mixture with salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and simmer a few minutes.
To serve, remove bay leaves and serve with croutons.

title: eggless raisin cake
directions: In
saucepan
bring
to
boil,
water and raisins, then simmer 10
minutes.
Add
butter
and set aside to cool.
Mix flour, sugar,
soda,
salt,
cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend well into raisin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cranberry drops
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together.
Beat in milk, orange juice and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Blend well with sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and cranberries. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan bread
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together in a mixing bowl and stir in the pecans.
Beat eggs vigorously in a separate bowl until very thick; add the milk and stir into the flour-nut mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Turn out of the pan onto a cake rack and cool.
Keeps well wrapped in foil.

title: "escabeche de ayita"(husband approved, well worth the wait)
directions: Fry fish and set aside.

title: burt reynolds' parmesan garlic toast(makes 8 slices)
directions: Combine butter, cheese and garlic.
Pile mixture high on 8 thick slices of bread (or hard sliced rolls, or in a pinch, use English muffins).
Place the slices on a double thickness of aluminum foil.
Bake in hot oven at 400°
for 10 minutes.
Garnish with a dash of paprika.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix until smooth and add dressing mix.
Pour onto wax paper that has chopped pecans on it.
Form into a ball and cover with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles (follow directions on the box), drain and rinse.
In a large skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until brown.
Drain the fat and add the spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer.

title: mini reubens
directions: Mix sauerkraut and dressing in a bowl and put aside.
Unroll crescent rolls as directed and place on cookie sheet.
Cut corned beef into triangle shapes and place on crescent roll.
Then cut Swiss cheese in triangles and place on top of corned beef.
Put one tablespoon of dressing mixture on top of the Swiss cheese. Roll up crescent roll with this filling.
Bake as directed on can. Serve when cooled.

title: steamed chicken with lemon
directions: Note:
The chicken can be individual pieces that you like such as legs.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put ingredients in pan as listed:

crushed pineapple, blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar sprinkled over berries, dry cake mix poured over blueberries, melted butter poured over cake mix, 1/4 cup sugar sprinkled over mix and pecans sprinkled on top.

title: chocolate pound cake(homemade)
directions: Cream together butter and shortening; add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Mix milk and vanilla flavoring together and add a little at a time with the flour.
Mix well and bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 80 minutes.
Cool and add frosting if you like (optional).

title: frozen chocolate pie
directions: Slowly	melt chocolate squares in small saucepan with 3 tablespoons milk, stirring frequently over very low heat.

title: red crest tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot tomatoes.
Add other ingredients; force through a sieve.
Pour into individual molds or a flat dish.
Just before it sets, shove a small ball of highly seasoned cream cheese into each serving.

title: fluffy party frosting
directions: Blend flour, milk and salt.
Cook until thick for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly for about 5 minutes.
Add the cooled flour paste and the vanilla, a small amount at a time.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Makes a large amount of frosting.

title: smoked sausage soup
directions: Cut up sausage in bite-size pieces and brown in skillet.
In a large pan, simmer all ingredients but potatoes and peppers for 1 hour, then add dried potatoes and green pepper.
Cook until done and soup thickens.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use small foil liners and small cupcake pans. Place one vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake liners.
Top wafer with cheese mixture 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool top with either cherry pie filling or blueberry pie filling.

title: cabbage slaw with yogurt dressing
directions: Shred cabbage about 1/4-inch thick.
Put in bowl. Trim ends and tops of radishes.
Slice and add to the cabbage.
Fold in the yogurt.
Taste.
Add sugar and salt, if desired.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: On stove, mix syrup and sugar; then pour in other ingredients. In a greased pan, mix all ingredients.
Freeze for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Saute basil, parsley and garlic in oil.
Add nuts and cheese last.
Cook and drain spaghetti and add butter.
Pour sauce over and toss.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix; form into ball
and
wrap	in waxed paper.
Chill. Remove and sprinkle with paprika.

title: squash fritters
directions: Add enough flour to make stiff batter . Drop from tablespoon into hot grease and fry on both sides until brown.
Serve hot.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: s'mores bars
directions: Combine the crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press half into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining crumb mixture; press firmly. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from the oven and immediately press top firmly with spatula.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: noma's cherry topped pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add sour cream.
Mix good. Pour over crushed vanilla wafers and top with can of cherry filling.

title: no-peek stew
directions: In large casserole dish mix together.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
No peeking!

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes until there are no lumps.
Add cream cheese and butter; beat well.
Add sour cream, eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat until fluffy.
Place in a 9-inch casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes in oven, uncovered, until lightly browned, about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Roll crackers.
Put half of crumbs in bottom of casserole. Cook broccoli according to directions.
Put on top of crumbs.
Mix soup with milk; pour on broccoli.
Put on rest of crumbs on cheese mixture.
Melt margarine; pour over top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped tuna and potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, slice and boil in salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in pan; blend with flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook over low heat until thick and smooth. Arrange potatoes, tuna and onions in alternating layers in a greased casserole dish.
Pour sauce all over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caesar pasta salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and cool. Add broccoli, cauliflower, cucumber and red pepper.
Toss salad with Caesar salad dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Chill.
To serve, squeeze lemon juice over salad; garnish with cherry tomatoes and fresh parsley.

title: curried rice-bean salad
directions: Combine rice, beans, onions, green pepper, celery and parsley. Toss to mix.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly with rice mixture.
This mixture can be served loose in a lettuce-lined bowl.
Or it can be pressed into a 5-cup ring mold, chilled, unmolded and brought back to room temperature just before serving.
Fill center of ring with cherry tomatoes or watercress.

title: peggy's chicken
directions: Wrap 1 strip of bacon around rolled half of chicken breast. Put 8 pieces of breast in casserole which has been covered with one layer of chipped beef.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Do not add salt as bacon and chipped beef supply enough. Cook uncovered 3 hours in 300° oven.
Bacon and chipped beef will be almost absorbed, chicken will be juicy inside.
Can leave in oven 1 hour after heat is turned off, so it is great for company.

title: chocolate frosting for cookies
directions: Combine melted Crisco, cocoa and salt, then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin, if needed.

title: bunny punch
directions: Serve over crushed ice with a large plastic straw.

title: elsie and daisy's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and cream.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add chocolate morsels.
Mix.
Add marshmallows, add peanut butter; beat until glossy.
Pour into greased cookie sheet or any old pan will do that is flat and at least 1 1/2 to 2-inches deep.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add apples and mix.
In a separate bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients.
Add to apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate.

title: honey-lime marinated steak
directions: Combine lime juice and next 5 ingredients and pour over steak. Refrigerate for 24 hours, turning steak occasionally.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving marinade.
Coat grill with cooking spray.
Grill steak 5 to 6-inches over coals for 6 to 7 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Cut diagonally into thin slices and serve.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix in food processor, blender or mixer. Chill.

title: clara's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in glass baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix until dough is stiff.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: homemade hot cocoa
directions: Combine the following in large pot:
sugar,
1/2 cup water, cocoa and vanilla.
Heat over medium heat and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Add evaporated milk and 1 cup water.
Reheat and serve.

title: cheese logs
directions: Grind cheese; mix all together.
Add hot sauce, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce with cheese.
Roll into logs and roll in pecans that have some paprika and chili powder in it. Refrigerate.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix the ingredients together; shape into meatballs.
Place in a baking dish.
Combine the sauce ingredients; pour over the meatballs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 45 meatballs.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts, vanilla and bananas.
Bake in two greased floured loaf pans at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese well.
Add sugar gradually. Beat in egg yolk, vanilla extract and orange rind.
Sift flour with salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fill cookie press.
Form cookies on ungreased sheets.
Decorate with colored sugar, cinnamon, etc.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add the next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Heat until bubbly.
Tear tortillas into fourths; place in casserole dish so a layer covers.
Spoon half of meat over tortillas.
Put on another layer of tortillas.
Add remaining meat and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash stew
directions: Cook bacon in large stewpot.
Remove bacon; set aside.
Add squash to pot.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Crumble bacon and add to pot.
Stew for 2 hours.

title: shower cake
directions: Make cake as directed; let cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding; spread this on top of cool cake.
Top with drained pineapple.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Drain cooked peas or open package of frozen peas to thaw.
Mix all ingredients and serve on salad greens.
Tomato wedges may be used as garnish.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add cereals and oats.
Bake 10 minutes or until slightly brown at 350°.
Makes four dozen cookies.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear cleaned lettuce into small pieces.
Place in 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top.
Top with grated cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Simmer chopped onion in margarine. Add melted garlic cheese and remaining ingredients.
Serve hot in a chafing dish with crisp crackers.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown onion and beef in margarine.
Mix cornstarch and spices into pizza sauce.
Add to meat.
Stir well.
When mixture bubbles and thickens, add cheese by thirds.
Keep warm.
Dip cubed French bread or garlic bread.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Mix melted margarine and flour together.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Add eggs, cottage cheese, onion, Cheddar cheese and broccoli.
Mix well.
Bake in greased deep dish pie plate for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese balls
directions: Work butter and cheese together at room temperature.
When mixture is smooth, work in flour, salt, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
(You can freeze them.)

title: paella
directions: Rinse mussels well.
Place in a pot of boiling water to which a little lemon juice and onion has been added and boil about 5 minutes.
(Buy only mussels which are closed.
Store in refrigerator in open container.
Once they are boiled, they should be open; if not, throw away.)
Drain mussels, reserving 4 cups of the liquid.
Separate each mussel into 2 halves, discarding the half shell which has no meat. Meanwhile, saute onion and garlic until tender in plenty of olive oil in a paella pan or a very large skillet.
Rinse and drain shrimp, leaving on shells.
Add to pan and cook until pink, stirring frequently.
Then add the rice and saute a little.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil one large pot of water; add noodles.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Place noodles in large casserole dish. Add tuna by using fork to shred tuna into smaller pieces from can. Add mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Add salt and mix once again. Place in preheated oven (350°).
Cook for 1/2 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning; spread in dish.
Pour salsa and spread.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Layer lettuce, onions, cheese and then tomatoes.
Dip with taco chips.

title: taylor's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars and cream together until fluffy. Mix in egg.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place on baking rack until completely cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken with 1 onion and bay leaf until done.
Remove chicken and vegetables; reserve liquid.
Saute bell pepper, celery and mushroom in margarine.
Add soup and milk.
Bring to a boil. Meanwhile, cut up chicken breasts into bite size pieces.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Spoon out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Beat sugar, egg and oil.
Add baking soda, flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets; bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Batter will be quite soft.

title: chili supper
directions: Brown meat until crumbly.
Drain off most of fat.
Pour into a large pot or crock-pot and add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; then lower heat and simmer for approximately 2 hours or until of desired consistency.
The tomato sauce will make a thicker chili than the tomatoes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients just before serving.

title: creamy chicken breasts
directions: In greased baking dish, place some dried beef slices under each chicken breast.
Cut bacon strips in half; place on top of each breast in an X. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked family style pasta
directions: In frying pan brown the beef, oil and garlic.
Saute until meat is cooked.
Drain.
Add the spaghetti sauce, gravy, Parmesan, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer the mixture while you cook the pasta in 4 quarts of boiling water until barely tender.
Drain the pasta and mix with the sauce.
Pour into a large baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut crust off bread.
Cut each slice into 5 or 6 strips.
Put crust and strips in separate pans and bake at 250° for 1 hour. Turn oven off and let stand for 15 minutes or longer.
Roll crust edges into crumbs.
Make fine with rolling pin.
Mix peanut butter and oil.
Blend to creamy consistency.
Dip strips in this mixture, scraping off surplus.
Roll in crumbs.
Let dry.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs together with wooden spoon, don't use mixer.
Add pineapple.
Mix well with spoon.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Check middle with toothpick.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: mocha brownies
directions: In a large bowl combine flour and sugar. In a heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee and cocoa. Stir and heat to boiling. Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Mix well at high speed with electric mixer. Pour into greased 17 X 11 jelly roll pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: baked okra
directions: Wash okra good and while wet, slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Add salt, cornmeal and flour.
Stir this in with a spoon.
Have ready 1 medium size, hot frypan that has bacon drippings.
Let okra heat 2 or 3 minutes, then stir lightly.
Place on top of okra the 1 pat of butter.
Set this pan of okra in hot oven.
Cook only 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber delights
directions: Empty beets and their liquid into a small saucepan; add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Heat just until the sugar dissolves; cool to room temperature.
Put the eggs in a medium size bowl (or in a half gallon preserving jar).

Pour in the beet mixture and add just enough of the water so that the liquid covers the eggs. Cover and marinate 2 to 3 days in the refrigerator before serving, stirring now and then or inverting the jar gently a few times. (This colors the eggs evenly and adds flavor.)
To serve, spoon beets, eggs and some liquid into a serving bowl.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: Put barley in saucepan. Cover with water and bring to a boil. Drain and rinse. Put all ingredients except vegetables in crock-pot and cover with water. Cook on medium until meat is tender. Add vegetables and serve.

title: old fashion coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage; add chopped hot peppers. Mix together equal amounts of vinegar and water. Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste. Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pineapple (not drained).
Bake in Bundt pan according to directions on cake mix box.
Do not add water; these are the only 2 ingredients.

title: grilled fish oriental
directions: Combine pressed garlic, ginger, oil, rice vinegar and shoyu in a small bowl.
Place fish in a nonreactive container.
Pour sauce over.
Let fish stand for 20 minutes.
Grill or broil fish, basting frequently.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: pepper-onion relish
directions: Drain pepper and onions.
Combine all ingredients and bring slowly to a boil.
Cook until slightly thickened, about 25 minutes.
Pour into clean, hot, sterilized jars.
Fill jars to 1/2 inch of top.
Seal.
Process 10 minutes at simmering temperature, about 180 degrees.

title: spring onion roll-ups
directions: Cut green tops from onions and throw away.
Take 1 slice of ham, spread with cream cheese.
Place a spring onion at one end. Put enough ham over it to hold it and roll it up.
Cut into 1/4 or 1/2-inch slices and put on a dish on top of a Ritz cracker.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add can of kidney beans with liquid and simmer 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool completely.
Just before serving, combine meat and bean mixture, lettuce, onions, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos.
Add dressing and mix well.
The last addition is sprinkling of taco powder seasoning and tossing gives it that peppy zest!
Good for showers and parties.
Bon Appetit!

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Break bread into pieces and place in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Add raisins and cinnamon.
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt and vanilla. Warm milk; pour into egg mixture and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, until inserted knife blade comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold with cream and sugar.

title: chicken bake
directions: Put rice in bottom of pan. Arrange salted and peppered chicken on top.
Add soups and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: fruit and nutty prune loaf
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine with sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Combine in blender prunes, water, egg and orange juice. Blend well, then mix it in with dry ingredients.
Add nuts. Mixture will be lumpy.
Grease small loaf pans, about 6. Spoon mixture in and place pans on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued lamb
directions: Mash garlic; mix all ingredients.
Add to following: Debone leg of lamb.
Take out all fat which will separate meat into many smaller pieces.
Marinate in Tupperware type product from 24 hours to several days.
Grill pieces on gas grill.

title: mattie sue's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix with tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with love and service.
Add 4 cups prayer and faith.
Bake well in human kindness.
Serve with a smile.
Author unknown.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, juice and flavoring.
Add mixed dry ingredients.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Roll into 6-inch to 8-inch lengths about 2-inches thick.
Bake on greased and floured cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Slice on an angle about 1-inch wide.
(You may retoast after cutting if you like them hard.)

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares and garnish with pecans, if desired.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Trim the edges of the bread;
cut into cubes.
Put half into a 9
x
12-inch baking dish.
Add cream cheese, then rest of bread cubes
to
dish.
Add mixture of eggs, syrup and milk to the cubes.
Cover
and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: bread with dill dip
directions: Use dark bread that has been hollowed out.
Pumpernickel is fantastic, or rye or white.
Fill cavity in hollowed out bread with dip.
Cut up or break into chunks the bread left over.
Use for dipping.
Refrigerate dip in bread bowl for 4 hours.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt and baking soda.
Then add beaten egg and fruit.
Pour batter in greased small square pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is so easy and sooo good!

title: russian cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pineapple and vanilla until blended. Add flour, soda and nuts. Mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: flying fish(squash or pumpkin blossoms)
directions: Wash blossoms in salt water
and
drain.
Beat eggs and 1/8 teaspoon salt together in
dish.
Dip
blossoms
in
this mixture, then in fine cracker crumbs.
Cook	in
hot, deep fat over a medium burner.
Brown on
both sides, being careful not to burn.

title: pumpkin seeds(microwave)
directions: Cut the top from a pumpkin and scoop out the seeds.
Wash seeds, remove connecting fibers and pat dry.
Toss 2 cups of raw seeds with the oil and 3 salts.
Combine in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cook in microwave oven on High, uncovered, for 8 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Cool.

title: sicilian sesame cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Moisten the seed with the water in a small bowl, set aside.
Mix the dry ingredients together, then cut in the shortening.
Stir in the eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Roll out the dough into logs, the same thickness as a soft pretzel.
Cut into two-inch pieces and roll pieces in the seeds.
Place onto greased baking sheets, 1 inch apart, and bake for 10-12 minutes.

title: 7-up applesauce jello(no fat, low sugar)
directions: Heat applesauce.
Dissolve jellos in applesauce.
Let cool. Add 7-Up and refrigerate.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour and brown in oil with one sliced onion. Add water and bay leaves.
Simmer for one hour.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Add vegetables and cook until tender (30 to 40 minutes).
If desired, add one tablespoon cornstarch to 1/4 cup cold water, then add to gravy to thicken.

title: swiss fillets
directions: Grease baking dish.
Pepper and salt fish fillets.
On each fillet, place 2 slices Swiss cheese.
Cover with 2 remaining fillets.
Flour lightly and sprinkle paprika.
Dot with butter and bake at 400° for at least 15 minutes or until fish flakes off easily.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Knead ingredients until well mixed.
Roll into one inch balls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: easy chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine eggs and shortening.
Add half of dry mix.
Combine thoroughly.
Add remainder of mix and nuts; combine thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool; frost if desired.

title: home fries
directions: Pressure cook the potatoes for 5 minutes or bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 1/4-inch wedges.
Deep fry in hot oil until brown.
Season with pepper and salt.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add ingredients in layers as listed.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: pan apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and egg.
Add dry ingredients alternating with coffee.
Add apples.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Top with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
May put topping in cake to make richer and give more flavor.

title: pepper pot soup
directions: Simmer ham bone in enough water to cover for 2 hours.
Remove bone and add tomato juice, tomato soup, sliced carrots, diced onions,crushed red peppers, pepper and seasoning salt.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat, and add ham and rice. Simmer on low heat until rice is soft.
If soup is too thick, add water to desired consistency.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in small cubes.
Add salt, pepper and Season-All. Toss until well seasoned.
Layer in oblong casserole dish.
Should be in single layer for best results.
Pour butter or margarine over potatoes.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve 2 to 3 teaspoons of mixture for each cup of hot water.
Good especially in cold weather.

title: creamed cauliflower casserole
directions: Preheat oven
to
Lightly
oil
a 1-quart baking dish. Wash
cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Parboil in small amount of
water 8 to 12 minutes; drain.
Combine cauliflower, lo-fat
milk,
onion and seasonings in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Turn
mixture
into prepared baking dish.	Bake in preheated oven
20	to
25 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jim and kathy countryman's ham loaf
directions: Mix together and put in oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with Horseradish Sauce on the side.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in 2-quart glass mixing bowl until well blended.
Add butter.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Stir once.
Microwave 5 minutes more on High.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate bits and nuts until well blended and marshmallows melted.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cool until set.
Cut into 30 squares.

title: hot quiche appetizer
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over rolls and cheese.
Sprinkle bacon and onions on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let set a few minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: feta cumin corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into a large bowl, sift together the corn meal, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cumin.
Add the Feta and scallion; toss the mixture well.
In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, sugar and oil.
Add milk mixture to corn meal mixture.
Stir batter until it is just combined.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake in middle of oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Let the corn bread cool in the pan on a rack for 5 minutes.
Run a thin knife around the edges of pan.
Turn bread out onto rack.
Let cool completely.

title: fruity bran muffins
directions: Mix Bran and juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg, oleo and fruit.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Stir into bran mixture just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining mix with butter and 1 egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Press in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sheepherder lamb shanks
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Add 2 cups water. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for 1 more hour or until meat is very tender and sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.
Wonderful with warm sourdough bread and tossed green salad.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg thoroughly. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover dough; chill for about 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls; place three inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet; with fork dipped in flour, flatten balls in a crisscross design.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: quick chili
directions: In large skillet, heat oil. Add beef. Cook. Stir in chilli seasoning mix. Add water, tomatoes and beans. Bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
cook
on top of stove.
When thick put in
cooked pie shell and put egg whites on top of pie and brown in oven at 350°.

title: ribbon nut bread
directions: A center of sweetened cream cheese makes this nut bread a sumptuous treat.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Bring oleo, water and cocoa to boil; pour over flour mixture.
Mix in eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for about 45 minutes.

title: scrambled egg jack
directions: Dice raw bacon; put in frying pan.
Use medium heat; cook to desired doneness.
Drain grease.
Mix eggs and milk in bowl, then add to the bacon in frying pan.
Scramble as usual.
Remove from pan; salt and pepper to taste.
Feeds 4.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt fat in pan.
Brown onion, pepper and meat in hot fat. Remove from heat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Return to heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, adding water if necessary.
Add beans and heat for 30 minutes longer.

title: herb tuna casserole
directions: Arrange tuna in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add peas. Combine in a separate bowl the cream of mushroom soup, milk, sherry and seasonings.
Pour half over the first mixture.
Put noodles over this.
Add rest of mixture.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Add all the ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet pepper chowder
directions: In soup kettle, combine the broth, potatoes, carrots, celery and onion; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add the peppers; return to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.

title: meat and tater pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cornflakes, salt, pepper, mustard and milk in large bowl; beat well.
Add meat; mix gently.
Press evenly on bottom and sides of pan.
Beat the eggs.
Add potatoes, onion and parsley.
Stir; spread on meat mixture.
Bake in a 9-inch pie plate at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes. Put in jars and seal. Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: beef stew
directions: Sprinkle
beef
with salt, sugar and pepper.
Brown well in oil.
Add
water and bouillon cubes.
Cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until
meat is almost tender.
Stir in 57 sauce and vegetables. Cover.
Simmer
hour
or until vegetables are tender. Thicken with a flour and water mixture.

title: vinegar pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt. Work in shortening until mixture is the consistency of cornmeal. Bet egg lightly; add water and stir, then add vinegar. Blend into flour mixture to form a soft dough. Gather into a ball. Cut in half. Chill for 10 to 15 minutes. Flour board well and roll each half into a circle 1-inch larger than pie pan. Fit into pan and flute edges.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 375° to 400° (hot).
Heavily grease 6 deep custard cups or 8 muffin cups.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, flour and salt.
Stir with fork just until smooth.
(Do not overbeat.)
Fill greased custard cups 1/2 full or fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 60 minutes or until deep, golden brown.
Remove from cups immediately and serve.
Yield: 6 to 8 popovers.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Tip:
Aluminum foil can be used to shield the corners of a square dish, if used.
Be sure it is folded smoothly over the corners.
If used, remove during the High phase of cooking.
Check for doneness with a toothpick but be careful not to check in a spot that has a chocolate chunk.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Heat oil, at least 1 inch in frying pan.
Using a large funnel, fill with small portion of mixture.
Let mixture run through spout into hot oil, forming figures of 8 or your own design.
Brown, turn, brown other side.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt margarine in nonstick skillet.
Mix half and half or creamer with flour.
Pour into skillet and stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Beat eggs and small amount of white sauce from skillet with eggs to temper.
Then add eggs to skillet and stir until blended and smooth.
Add seafood and heat through. Add wine and lemon juice and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve over rice or toast.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add pineapple (undrained) and pie filling.
Stir.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix remaining ingredients (except nuts) and spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: yeast dough
directions: Put yeast, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Dissolve with 1 cup hot water (about coffee drinking temperature).
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add oil and mix in flour 1/2 cup at a time, mixing it well.
Knead dough until it is smooth.
Put in clean bowl, cover with towel and let it rise until it is double the size it first was. Knead it some more and shape into loaves.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, then cut back heat to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into zipper bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside bag.
Seal bag securely.
Shake bag until pieces are evenly coated.
Pour into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 3 1/2 minutes. Stop and stir every minute.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, vanilla and poppy seed.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in ungreased angel cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not frost.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket fat side up in baking pan.
Mix Coke, chili sauce and soup mix together.
Pour over brisket.
Cover with foil. Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Slice across grain of meat and serve!

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake cake according to package directions.
Let cool. Split layers.
Ice between each layer, but don't ice the sides. Keep in refrigerator 3 or 4 days before eating.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly and put in kettle with water to cover. Add salt to taste and bay leaf; cook.
Meanwhile, wash and prepare celery, onion, potatoes, carrots and peas.
When chicken is about half done, remove bay leaf and add the cut up vegetables. Cook on low heat until done.
Remove chicken; leave in pieces or remove skin and bones and cut up in smaller pieces.

title: turnovers
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening in mixing bowl.
Add milk and vinegar; mix well.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Fill lower right-hand corner with filling (2 to 3 tablespoons).
Pull top left over filling; meet edges and pinch. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool on pan.
Can be topped with glaze.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cook, stirring occasionally.
After it boils, reduce heat to low.
Top with cheese when served.
Add chicken or beef if desired.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
(Should be enough for 4 layers.)
Pour into cake pans.
Bake at 375°.
Let cool before frosting.

title: ortega bread
directions: Mix and pour into greased oblong pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cracker cookies
directions: You will need sheet of aluminum foil.

title: punch
directions: Make 2 packages of Kool-Aid as per directions.
Mix pineapple juice and Jell-O mix.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale over this mixture with softened sherbet.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: elegant chicken breasts
directions: Lay breasts on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese slice on each breast.
Mix soup, wine and milk and pour over.
Process butter and stuffing to mix (or melt butter and mix by hand). Sprinkle over breasts and bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Serves 4.

title: cabbage & ramen salad
directions: Toast sesame seeds and almonds in 350 degree oven for about 10 minutes.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper, salt and flavor packet and let stand 2 hours.
Toss cabbage and onions.
Just before serving, add dressing, sesame seeds, almonds and crushed noodles.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and set aside.
Cook 1 pound hamburger and 1 large onion (diced).
Drain well.
Grease large iron skillet and heat.
Sprinkle thin layer of corn meal in skillet.
Brown.
Pour 1/2 of batter in skillet.
Sprinkle 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese evenly over batter.
Add hamburger, onions and 2 or 3 jalapeno chopped peppers over cheese.
Pour remaining batter over cheese, hamburger, onions and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: brownie cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add chips and stir until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat, add sugar and eggs and stir until blended.
Add flour, stir until blended. Pour into cupcake pan lined with cups, 24 large cupcakes or 36 mini cupcakes.
Bake until tops look cracked.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes for mini cups and 25 to 30 minutes for large cups.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil, mash and strain potatoes, then measure.
Add butter and milk.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with sugar.
Add to potatoes. Beat whites stiff and fold into potatoes.
Pour into pie crust and bake 30 minutes in moderate oven or until done.
Brush over the pastry with cooking oil or melted shortening before putting in the mixture.
This prevents the crust from getting soggy.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Will be thick. Pour onto hot griddle.

title: montana chile
directions: Saute the onions in a large pan.
Add the ground beef and brown.
Mix in the remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl mix remaining ingredients well.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from tins.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: breakfast-brunch casserole
directions: Layer hash browns, cheese, onion, sausage and mushrooms in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over layers and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until set and brown on top.

title: two meal meat loaf
directions: Mix together soup mix, eggs, ketchup, water and bread crumbs. Add ground chuck tenderly and form into 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Use one loaf for a meal and the other for cold or hot sandwiches for another meal.
Good with mashed or baked potatoes, gravy, salad and applesauce.

title: easy cheesy apples
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add grated cheese and flour.
Place sliced apples in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread creamed mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes uncovered.

title: cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw vegetables.
Butter dish.
Mix rice, onion, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Add vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage; let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Mix cabbage, pepper, carrot and celery.
Mix vinegar, salt, sugar, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture; package to freeze.
When defrosting, do it in refrigerator.

title: dip
directions: Cut beef in small pieces; mix with other ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar well.
Mix pineapple, strawberries (with juice), bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Add to cream cheese.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: ruth's rice
directions: Mix rice well with sugar.
Add pineapple, egg and half and half.
Put in lightly greased baking dish.
Add milk until soupy. Stir well.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz with 1/2 stick butter.
Pour over Veg-All.
Add cracker crumbs.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over this.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls one-half the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil, making sure all the butter is melted.
Add to flour and salt mixture and mix well.
Add one egg at a time, beating until smooth.
Spread on a jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Burst bubbles after coming out of the oven.

title: stir and roll pie crust
directions: In small bowl, stir salad oil and milk all at once into flour and salt mixture.
Mix thoroughly, but gently (the less handling the better).
Roll half of the dough between two sheets of waxed paper.
Place in a 9-inch pie pan.
Roll other half for top crust. Makes enough for a 9-inch double crust.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan melt butter;
remove from heat and blend in flour, salt and mustard.	Add milk; heat, stirring constantly until sauce
thickens
a little and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; heat until melted, stirring occasionally.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: Blend corn syrup, butter and salt.
Add sugar.
Mix with spoon and hands until smooth.
Divide into thirds.
Knead red food color into 1/3 mixture, green food color into 1/3 mixture and leave 1/3 mixture white.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with fork on wax paper.
Let dry several hours.

title: spanakapitta
directions: In frying pan, fry the onions and mushrooms together until cooked.
In a separate bowl, add together the cooked spinach (ensure the spinach is well drained before adding other ingredients), almonds, eggs, bread crumbs, dill, nutmeg and Feta cheese.
Add the mushroom and onion mixture.
Set aside.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar. Pour into pie pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
When cooled completely, put a topping of Cool Whip and shaved chocolate over it; refrigerate.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in pan, set aside.
Mix margarine, vanilla and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add flour and salt.
Pour into a greased and floured 9x12-inch Pyrex.
Pour chocolate over top of brownies and swirl into batter.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 min.

title: oyster fritters
directions: After draining oysters, add the salt, pepper and baking powder to the oysters.
Mix well. Add flour and stir thoroughly until mixture has a smooth appearance.
Spoon oyster mixture into a frying pan of hot Crisco.
Makes about 8 fritters.

title: aunt martha's angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixed thoroughly. Add milk and dissolved yeast.
Work together with a large spoon until all flour is moist. Cover bowl and refrigerate until needed.
This dough will keep for several days in the refrigerator.
Roll out on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter. Let double in size and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 475°.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate bits when everything else is well beat.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.

title: holliberry punch
directions: Mix and put in punch bowl.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown beef in a 10-inch skillet; add the remaining ingredients. Cover and cook for 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut
potatoes
into quarters.
Combine potatoes, flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Shake
in
a
bag.
Melt butter in a long baking dish.
Place potatoes in dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn
potatoes
after 30 minutes.
When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: You will need a mixer.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, butter and cream until it forms a soft ball in cool water.
Add vanilla and dates and beat until lukewarm.
Add pecans and roll into a loaf and store in refrigerator until the next day.
Slice.

title: hot fruit casserole(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Arrange drained fruit in layers in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cream oleo, sugar, cornstarch and curry powder. Crumble mixture on top of fruit. Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Place green or red cherries on top when the casserole is nearly done.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Boil potatoes until tender. Mix together next 5 ingredients and set aside.
Drain potatoes and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour the soup mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and place crushed potato chips on top.

title: spinach potatoes
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, sugar, margarine, salt, pepper and onion.
Thaw spinach and drain well. Add to potato mixture.
Place in 2 baking dishes.
Sprinkle Cheddar over top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
One dish can be frozen and baked later after thawing.

title: meijer's turkey vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth; set aside.
In skillet in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry the turkey until browned.
Remove; set aside.
In skillet in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry vegetables with garlic until tender-crisp.
Reduce heat to medium; stir in the turkey and the broth mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan; cook until soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm.
Beat to spreading consistency, then frost cake.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add onion and celery.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Stir in kraut, noodles, soup and mushrooms; season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Meat will be tender.
Different and good.

title: salted cod catalana style
directions: The cod is available in Latin American grocery stores and should have been desalted by slightly cooking it in water several times (using fresh water each time).
However, regular cod can also be used, in which case you'd add at least a teaspoon of salt.
Once the sofrito is cooked, you add the cooked garbanzos, the toasted almonds and the sliced cod.
Cook over low heat until flaky.
Place on serving tray over slices of toasted or fried bread slices. Decorate with red pimentos.

title: norfolk noodles(great with cranberry chicken)
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions. Drain. While noodles are still hot, mix in remaining ingredients, except Cheddar and paprika. Place in shallow baking dish. Top with cheese and sprinkle paprika. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda in a large bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Beat eggs in small bowl; add sour cream and milk.
Stir in lemon juice, sugar and lemon zest.
Add to flour mixture, mixing just until moistened. Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix orange juice and cream cheese.
Fold in marshmallow cream. Chill.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake yellow cake on an 11 x 15-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix together cheese, instant pudding and milk; spread on cooled cake. Mix crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pudding mix and top with coconut.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs, vanilla, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Combine flour and oatmeal and stir into sugar mixture. Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Mix cornstarch or flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together and toss with pears until well coated.
Place in uncooked pastry.
Dot with oleo or butter.
Over the top, add top lattice or strip crust.
Cook about 45 minutes at 350° or until crust is browned.

title: party mix
directions: Mix Accent, celery salt, garlic salt, parsley and onion salt. Combine butter, cereals, pretzel sticks and nuts.
Pour spices over cereal mixture.
(Use roaster lid to combine and bake ingredients.)
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir about every 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pastry shell.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: grandma's homemade vegetable soup
directions: Your first step is to make medium sized balls with your ground beef.
Then you mix all the ingredients in the pot, but make sure that the tomato sauce is the very last thing.
Put the lid on the pot and bring to a boil, then turn heat to medium and let it cook for 2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together;
add egg yolks and 1 egg. Mix well.
Add milk and mix.
Put into	pie crust and top with meringue.

title: broccoli-ham hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Spoon rice into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place broccoli on rice.
Melt butter or margarine, sprinkle 2 tablespoon over bread crumbs and set aside.
Saute onion in remaining butter or margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stirring constantly; stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Add ham and heat through.
Pour over rice and broccoli in casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle on cheese and let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Mix Cool Whip and sour cream with pudding.
Slice strawberries and mix with glaze.
Layer strawberries, pudding and vanilla wafers.

title: spinach and orange salad("delicious")
directions: Wash, trim and dry spinach. Refrigerate.
Heat 1/2 cup sugar in small skillet over medium heat until sugar melts.

Add almonds and heat, stirring constantly, until almonds become caramelized. Cool on foil or waxed paper. Chop into bite size pieces. Tear spinach into bite size pieces. Toss with almonds, oranges, celery and onions. Combine salt, 2 tablespoons sugar, vinegar, oil, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
To serve, pour over salad and toss.

title: syrup pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients with eggbeater or electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Fold in 1 cup pecans.
Line two pie tins with unbaked pastry and pour in mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes. Let stand in tins until cool.

title: trail mix bar
directions: Grease 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
In 4-quart saucepan over low heat, heat marshmallows and butter until melted, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in popped corn, cereal, pretzels and 1/2 cup candies until blended.
Spoon into dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup M&M's.
Press with lightly greased hands.
Cool. Do not refrigerate.
Cut into 20 bars.

title: reese's balls
directions: Hand mix the first 4 ingredients.
Roll into small balls and freeze.
Dip in mixture of 1/2 paraffin and chocolate.

title: little horns
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide dough into 8 parts; cover with plastic wrap.
Chill overnight.
Roll each part into a circle on surface dusted with powdered sugar; roll to about less than 1/4-inch thick.
Cut circle as in cutting a pie.
Spread thinly with filling and roll up starting with wide end.
Brush horns with egg white; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sunshine swizzle punch
directions: Empty Crystal-Lite lemonade mix into large punch bowl.
Add club soda and lemonade concentrate; stir until completely dissolved.
Spoon 6 scoops (1-quart tub) raspberry sherbet into punch just before serving.
Makes 18 servings, 1 cup each.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Mix in a larger bowl the next 5 ingredients, then add the first bowl to the second bowl, then add the last three ingredients. Drop 1-inch ball on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
(Do not bake longer than 8 minutes.
Will be hard.
May not look done but will after cooling.)

title: "all-bran" dinner rolls
directions: Add boiling water to All-Bran, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Cool. Then add eggs, yeast (dissolved in warm water) and flour.
Mix well in large bowl and cover.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Next day while chilled, knead, roll out 1/2-inch thick, cut with biscuit cutter, butter lightly, fold and place in pan to rise until double.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Store in fridge or freezer.
Warm, uncovered, 7 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican style casserole
