directions: Line the bottom of a large rectangular baking dish with tortilla chips. Flatten chips with palm of hand. Put cooked ground beef on top of chips. Mix soups and Ro-Tel and pour over meat layer. Slice cheese and use as top layer. Heat at 350 until hot and cheese is melted.

title: homos bitsheeni
directions: Boil chickpeas for 15 minutes and mash like potatoes. Mash and add garlic cloves and other ingredients, mixing together well. Serve in a flat dish; decorate with parsley.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a large saucepan until tender. Stir in next 10 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon about 1/2 cup of the chicken mixture in the center of each tortilla; roll up and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over tortillas. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave)
directions: Mix together ground beef, rice, egg, onion, 1/2 cup tomato sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Arrange peppers in baking dish. Fill with mixture.
Mix remaining tomato sauce, water and sugar.
Pour over peppers. Cover with a tight fitting lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.

title: gayla baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up, in single layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in shaker. Mix well and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes(compliments of lynn's mom!)
directions: Combine flour, soda, cocoa, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Then add oil, water, vanilla and vinegar.
Beat until smooth. Fill paper cups in muffin pans 1/2 full.
Add a heaping teaspoon of filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles(low-fat)
directions: Boil chicken, carrots and onion in water until done, approximately 50 minutes.
Take chicken out of pan.
Add noodles and cream of chicken soup to carrots and onions.
Cook and stir often until noodles are soft.
Cut chicken into small pieces and add to noodles, soup, carrots and onions.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes longer, stirring often.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: homemade "spray and wash"
directions: To ammonia, add dishwashing soap and water.
Shake well.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pie filling and pineapple. Refrigerate and allow to congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Put on top of congealed mixture.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, Cheez Whiz, rice and soup; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: parslied mushroom patties
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, mushrooms, flour, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and pepper; mix well.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Using 1/2 cup of mixture for each patty, shape mixture into 3 1/2-inch patties.
Using a spatula, place 4 patties at a time into hot oil; cook 3 to 4 minutes per side until brown.
Remove from skillet, drain on paper towels and keep warm in oven.
Yield: 8 patties.
Each pattie: 139 calories and 8 gm fat.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add the bananas, eggs, juice and orange rind.
Sift the dry ingredients together and fold into the banana mixture.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 1 teaspoon per cup of boiling water.

title: vegetable collage
directions: Cook frozen vegetables separately and drain well.
Arrange all of the vegetables in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together the whipped cream and mayonnaise and spoon over the vegetables.
Sprinkle top with the grated cheese.
Bake casserole at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated and brown on top.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and syrup; mix in oats and vanilla. Spread into heavily greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until golden in middle and lightly browned around edges, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread over cooled bars.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes 36 bars.

title: spicy cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in salad bowl, mixing well.
Blend remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Pour over vegetables, tossing to mix.
Chill overnight.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, butter and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining semi-sweet chocolate chips over top.
Allow to stand until morsels become shiny.
Spread with spatula.
Let cool.
Chill 5 to 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer in large dish with wafers and bananas. Chill and serve.

title: french crumb cake
directions: Mix sour cream with soda; set aside.
Cream butter and egg yolks.
Add sugar.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Add dry mixture and sour cream alternately to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites.
Fold into batter.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle over batter.
Cut through batter with knife.
Pour into 8 x 11 1/2-inch greased pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a long greased baking dish, put pieces of chicken.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place pan in oven for 3 to 5 minutes, until margarine melts. Remove pan from oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Make sauce with milk and cheese in double boiler or heavy pan.
Add broccoli and mix well. Layer broccoli, cracker crumbs and butter in casserole dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican "stuff"
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add Sloppy Joes or taco mix, tomato paste and water.
Cook down until desired thickness.
Serve over Fritos. Garnish with diced tomatoes, chopped onions, shredded Cheddar cheese and shredded lettuce.
Looks awful, tastes good!

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook the broccoli with 1/2 teaspoon salt in the water in a saucepan until tender; drain.
Saute the onion in the margarine in a large skillet.
Add the soup, cheese, salt, m.s.g., pepper, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over medium heat until the cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Add the broccoli. Cook for 1 minute longer, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the mushrooms.
Cook until heated through.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.
May add 3/4 cup slivered almonds.
Yields 16 servings.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle green beans, mushrooms, onions, ham or chicken and cheese in a deep 10-inch pie plate.
In blender, place milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Blend for 15 seconds on high speed.
Pour over ingredients.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set for 5 minutes. Serve.

title: ann hines' spinach and artichokes
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake for 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
If you double, use 5 packages of spinach.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage & drain mix sausage, pork & beans & soup put in casserole dish; slice apple over top; sprinkle with brown sugar; bake at 350 for 1/2 hour.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Shape into loaf. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut loaf into 1/2-inch slices. Coat with flour. Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Put in casserole dish. Mix soup and 1/2 soup can of water.
Pour over meat. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix all canned ingredients together with meat and heat until bubbly.
Stir in chips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple and blackberry crumble
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine blackberries, sliced apples and sugar to taste.
Place in greased deep dish.
Mix flour, sugar and butter into a crumble.
Place over fruit and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until crumble is brown.
Cool and serve topped with whipped cream.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all together except Cheez Whiz.
Place in greased baking dish or pan and spoon Cheez Whiz onto.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When Cheez Whiz begins to brown, cover with foil for remainder of baking time.

title: country style omelette
directions: In a large skillet, saute the pork sausage until no longer pink, breaking up sausages.
Add the onion and butter.
Saute a few minutes longer until onion is soft, not brown.
Add the shredded potatoes.
Saute until soft.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and water and pour over sausage-potato mixture.
Cook on medium heat. As eggs begin to set, push cooked portion to center of pan.
When eggs are light brown on bottom and almost set on top, sprinkle with parsley or thyme.
Serve directly from pan with tomato salad. Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into bite size pieces and place in a greased 13x9x2 baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in dish.
Bake at 350 degrees 35 to 40 minutes Cheese will rise to top.
Mixture can be prepared night before and stored in refrigerator.
Bake right before serving.

title: georgia caviar
directions: Soak and cook peas.
Mix with remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and place in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with the bread and cheese. Drizzle with the melted butter. Bake uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until heated through. Yield: 5 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with chips or veggies. Mm-Mm good.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; beat eggs in well.
Add bananas; beat well again.
Add flour, soda and nuts until just blended.
Spoon in paper lined or well-greased and floured cupcake pans.
Makes 10 to 12.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: super-simple sunday roast
directions: Place roast in pan. Spread creamy onion soup over roast. Cover pan tightly with tinfoil. Bake in oven at 325° for approximately 2 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend 3 tablespoons of butter and stir in sugar.
In measuring cup, lightly beat 1 egg with fork and add enough milk to measure 3/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons and beat this mixture into the flour mixture.
Stir in blueberries and transfer the batter to a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Spread the batter evenly.

title: bishop's wine
directions: About 3 hours before serving, stick cloves in oranges and lemons. In a large kettle, combine 6 cups of wine, sugar and cinnamon sticks. Add clove-studded fruit. Cover; let stand until shortly before serving. Remove cover and bring just to a boil. Remove from heat, cover and steep 15 minutes. Remove fruit and cinnamon sticks, gently squeezing fruit (don't break peel). Add remaining wine; heat through. Serve hot. Makes 25 five ounce servings.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for chewy brownies. Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until set. Meanwhile, in large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in chips.
Pour into prepared pan.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Remove side of spring-form pan.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Prep time:
45 minutes.
Total time:
4 hours.
Makes one 9-inch cheesecake.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: After cutting fruit and nuts, mix thoroughly.
Press tightly in crock.
Let stand 1 week or ten days before cutting.
This keeps indefinitely.
Half of this recipe makes a good nice cake. Fruit balls can be made out of this recipe (part) also.
Takes about 1 teaspoon of fruit.
Roll into a ball, then roll in coconut.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, margarine and milk for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: tuna rice roll
directions: Cook rice in water until tender.
Turn into a large bowl and cool slightly.
Break tuna into large chunks and add to rice.
Stir in 1/3 cup of the soup.
Prepare pie crust.
Roll out on floured surface to 14 x 11-inch oval.
Spoon tuna mixture down center third of pastry.
Bring sides up and over filling to meet.
Press long edges together and pinch seam tightly with fingers.
Pinch each end of roll tightly until filling is completely enclosed.

title: biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: bayou scallops
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, except scallops.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add scallops and saute until all are fully cooked, but not overcooked. Makes 20 servings.

title: tab's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine butter or shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Stir and cook until dries out.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt chips in microwave pan for 3 minutes.
Take out and add condensed milk.
Stir until mixture is creamy.
Pour in nuts. Stir all together in Pam-sprayed pan and chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
May use any flavor chips.

title: casserole
directions: Grease baking dish and line bottom with Fritos.
Add chili. Place onion on top.
Bake at 400° until bubbly hot.

title: angel lemon custard
directions: Mix together in a double boiler. Cook until thick. Cool. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/2 cup sugar and fold into first mixture. Pour into baked crust. Put in oven until brown at 350°.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove from bones; reserve broth. Cut chicken into small pieces and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In saucepan, mix and bring to boil reserved broth and chicken soup.
In another bowl, combine margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly to form batter.
Pour soup and broth over chicken, then spoon batter on top to make crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Optional:
use canned peas and carrots in broth and soup.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, flavoring and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour in pie crusts and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease the bottom and sides of an 11 X 7 inch baking dish.
Chop the onions.
Heat butter in a small nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until melted.
Stir in onion.
Saute until tender.
Combine onion, chicken, soup, sour cream, milk and pimiento in a medium bowl and mix well.
Spoon mixture into prepared baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle baked layer with 3/4 cup of the cheddar. Arrange biscuits in single layer over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheddar.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown and the sauce is bubbly, about 20 minutes longer.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Place zucchini and onion in glass 4-quart casserole. Cover with ice water and salt. Let stand 1 hour; drain. Combine vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed, turmeric, dry mustard and mustard seed in a 1-1/2 quart glass casserole. Microwave on full power 8 to 10 minutes, or until mixture boils. Pour mix over zucchini and onions. Let stand covered 1 hour. Microwave, covered, on full power, for 15 minutes or until mixture boils a minimum of 3 minutes. Pack into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2 inch head space; add hot lids, process in boiling water bath 10 minutes plus 1 minute for each 1,000 feet above sea level. Remove jars to towel or rack. Cool overnight. Makes 4 pints.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let cheese soften.
Put in refrigerator. Then roll in pecans.
Put on crackers.

title: scones
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Spoon drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Makes 8.

title: oatmeal orange slice cookies
directions: Mix sugars with margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add orange slices to coat.
Add vanilla, dry ingredients and then add oats, coconut and pecans.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Steam onion, garlic, celery and pepper in bacon fat.
Add flour, salt, chili powder and sugar and brown like gravy.
Add water and simmer a few minutes.
Add tomatoes and vinegar and cook about 15 minutes.
Add cooked shrimp.
Serve on rice.

title: mexican sausage dip
directions: Fry sausage until brown. Pour off grease. Add cream cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Heat thoroughly. Serve with chips.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water and sugar in gallon jar.
Finish filling jar with pineapple juice.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add ginger ale and ice just before serving.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Beat well eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: kentucky wonder cake
directions: Beat German chocolate cake mix and next 3 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer 3 to 4 minutes or until creamy. Pour batter into a 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator. To serve, heat in double boiler.

title: pretzel crumb crust
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Press firmly into bottom and sides of a 1-inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool crust, then chill.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine margarine, corn syrup, peanut butter, salt and vanilla in large bowl.
Stir in powdered sugar gradually.
Turn onto board and knead until well blended and smooth.
Add nuts gradually, pressing and kneading into candy.
Press out with hands or rolling pin into square 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into serving pieces.
Yield: 2 pounds fudge.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes fine. Blend all ingredients and put in a buttered ovenproof dish. Bake until brown and bubbly at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese roll
directions: Melt cheese, add garlic and nuts.
Sprinkle chili powder on leaf paper and shape cheese into roll.
Roll in chili powder and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate.
Slice before serving.

title: light dilled potato salad
directions: In large bowl sprinkle corn oil and vinegar over potatoes. Toss lightly to coat.
Combine mayo, yogurt and mustard.
Add mayo mixture and remaining ingredients to potatoes.
Toss to coat well. Cover; chill.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Heat milk, sugar and salt on low until bubbly.
Dissolve cornstarch in milk.
Add to first mixture and also add eggs.
Cook until clear, about 10 minutes.
Remove from stove and add vanilla, margarine and peanut butter.
Whip smooth and cool a little before filling cooked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pooler punch
directions: In 2 gallon or larger container, combine all ingredients. Sweeten to taste. Chill before serving.

title: crab bisque
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and saute until soft.
Reduce to medium and add flour, whisking constantly until smooth.
Cook 5 minutes, whisking frequently.
Stir in parsley.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add sherry, crab and salt to taste and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not boil.
(Use cornstarch now to thicken to liking.) Serve hot.
Have crackers with it.
Serves 6.

title: filled minute steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay minute steaks out separated to thaw.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions.
Place a spoonful of stuffing on each minute steak.
Roll the minute steak up.

title: easy cinnamon buns
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch square pan.
Snip biscuits into quarters with kitchen shears and place in melted margarine.
Roll pieces with fork to completely coat them.
Blend sugar and cinnamon in small saucepan; add corn syrup.
Cook over low heat until sugar melts.
Stir in nuts and drizzle over biscuit pieces. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes until biscuits are well browned. Let stand 5 minutes then invert on serving plate.
Break buns apart with fork.

title: corn souffl
directions: Beat egg.
Add wet ingredients.
Stir in muffin mix.
Grease casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: glazed apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour batter into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on rack, right side up, for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except oleo.
Pour melted oleo over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 batter in 10-inch iron skillet.
Spread next 2 ingredients over this.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: state fair spinach
directions: Combine apple slices with orange juice in bowl.
Place spinach in salad bowl.
Drain apple slices, reserving 1/2 cup orange juice.
Arrange tomato wedges and apple slices over spinach. Sprinkle bacon and nuts in center.

title: auntie mickey's zucchini fritters(italian)
directions: Put everything in a large bowl and mix well with a fork.
Put salad oil in a frying pan (I use a Teflon coated pan) to cover the bottom about 1/4-inch high.
Heat until hot.
Drop tablespoonful of mixture into pan; cook until brown and carefully turn and cook second side.
Drain on brown paper bag or paper towels.
These taste wonderful warm or cold.
(I like them the second day cold from the refrigerator.)
This is great at a picnic.

title: swedish cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients by hand and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and cream them well.
Ice with the frosting and refrigerate.
It is better if it sets overnight and is served the following day.
It keeps well.

title: cathedrals
directions: Add chocolate to melted butter. Stir on low heat until melted. Cool enough so marshmallows won't melt when added. Add nuts. Let stand until it solidifies enough to form a log. Chill before slicing.

title: microwave fudge(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk together; add butter. Microwave 10 minutes. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallows. Stir and pour in pan to cool.

title: the crowd pleaser
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut into small pieces.
Combine artichoke pieces, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese in a medium-size bowl and mix thoroughly.
Transfer mixture into an ovenproof serving dish and sprinkle top with breadcrumbs. Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: soy sauced spiced beef
directions: Heat oil in saucepan over high heat.
Add beef, scallions and ginger.
Sear beef on all sides, being careful not to burn ginger and scallions.
Add sherry, soy sauce and sugar; mix well and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water; bring to boil.
Reduce to medium heat. Cover and cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add anise; reduce heat to low and cook 30 minutes more.
Serve hot or cold with rice.

title: skyline dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in pie plate.
Spread thawed chili over cream cheese.
Cover with cheese and bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips, Fritos, Doritos, etc.

title: peanut butter pralines
directions: Boil together buttermilk, butter and sugar until mixture reaches the soft-ball stage (240° on a candy thermometer). Add baking soda, vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until creamy and thick. Add peanuts and drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased paper.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, egg, oil and persimmon pulp (remove top of fruit and blend on high speed in blender).
Mix and add rest of the ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon to cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 10 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and water for three minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix. Add dry ingredients (which have been mixed together).
Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Artificial sweetener may be added to make cookies sweeter, but they are good and more healthy with only the fruit as sweetener.

title: chicken cacciatore with spaghetti(low-fat)
directions: In a large nonstick frying pan over medium heat, heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil.
Add 4 chicken breast halves and brown on both sides.
Remove to plate.
Repeat with remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and 4 chicken breast halves.
Add the onions and garlic. Saute 5 minutes until soft.
Add tomato sauce and stock.
Stir well.
Add chicken breasts and spoon sauce over them. Cover and cook 15 minutes, or until chicken is cooked.
Meanwhile, cook the spaghetti in a large pot of boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and place on a large platter.
Top with chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan.

title: cherry rhubarb crunch
directions: In a large bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, flour and salt. Mix well by hand.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2 cups of mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water; cook until mixture is thickened and clear.
Stir in extract and cherry filling.
Spoon over rhubarb.
Combine nuts with reserved crumbs mixture.
Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Beat butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, a little at a time, beating constantly.
Add lukewarm milk, a little at a time, still beating constantly.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat for at least 4 minutes, until sugar is broken down and frosting is of smooth consistency.

title: special k bars
directions: In a medium saucepan bring to a slow boil the syrup and sugar. Add peanut butter and cook until well blended.
Pour this over the cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: orange roughy
directions: Wrap each roughy filet in aluminum foil.
Add potatoes, green beans, carrots and onions to each filet.
Mix butter, lemon pepper, onion powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of each.
Close up the foil and bake at 320° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: great grandma's soft ginger cake
directions: Sift flour, soda,
ginger,
cinnamon and salt together. Cream sugar and shortening with molasses until well blended in a large bowl.
Add	dry sifted ingredients to bowl alternately with boiling water, beginning and ending with dry ingredients; stir in eggs.
Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven
at
350°	for 30 minutes or until center springs back when
pressed with fingertip.	Cool in pan at room temperature.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie dough or lemon bar crust in 9 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes. Cool. Mix cream cheese,
powdered sugar and vanilla together until there are no lumps. Add cool whip. Spread on cooled crust and top with fruit.

title: frogs eye salad
directions: In small pan, mix sugar, flour and salt and stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook moderately, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Cook pasta in 6 cups of water.
Boil only 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover.
Let set 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain at once and rinse with cold water.
Combine cooked mixture with pasta.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.
Stir rest in lightly. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: thrifty casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion. Drain fat. Add seasonings and soup.
Simmer 5 minutes. Combine mixture with vegetables.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole and top with mounds of potatoes. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dutch meatballs
directions: Form into small balls and saute quickly in 2 tablespoons of hot oil.
When meatballs are sauteed, put them all in skillet. Add 2 tablespoons tomato puree and 1 cup beef stock or bouillon. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Let stand for several hours or overnight. Just before serving, reheat, but do not boil.
Add 1 cup sour cream.

title: borscht
directions: In a pan with 2 tablespoons oil, brown 3 medium chopped onions, 2 medium grated carrots and 1 1/2 cups shredded cabbage. Stir until oil disappears. Add 6 ounces tomato paste and 2 beef bouillon cubes. In a second pan, boil 3 or 4 large beets. When they are tender, grate them. Cook 4 medium potatoes and cut into small pieces. In large pot, boil 1/4 pound soup meat and 4 quarts water. When meat is tender, add other items. Cook only 10 minutes. (Cooking longer discolors the soup.) Salt and pepper to taste and serve with a tablespoon of sour cream. A thin slice of lemon squeezed into each soup enhances the flavor.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes into sprayed casserole dish. Mix soup with milk in microwave container.
Microwave almost to boiling point.
To potatoes, sprinkle onions, salt, pepper and celery seed over.
Add mushrooms.
Top with soup mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Next, add flour, baking powder and milk.
Blend in blueberries.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
If you want to double the recipe, bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: potato hash
directions: Drain and squeeze grated potato.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl, except oil.
Over medium heat, put 1/8-inch oil in large skillet.
Pour 1 cup potato mix in pan.
Flatten slightly. Cook on both sides until crisp and brown (about 8 minutes).

title: hot chicken salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix chicken with soup, celery, water chestnuts and mayonnaise. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
Spread over the chicken.
Make the day before and refrigerate.

title: quick dumplings
directions: Empty soup in a large pot.
Add 4 soup cans of water and bring to a boil.
Mash biscuits and cut into 4 pieces each.
Add chicken and biscuit pieces to boiling soup and cook for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in cherries, chopped nuts, then whipped cream.
Let set in refrigerator before putting in chilled crumb crusts.
Makes 2 to 3 pies.

title: strawberry short pie
directions: Make crust per instructions on box.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1 cup boiling water.
Add salt and flour all at one time.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms ball.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well until smooth.
Do this until all eggs are beaten in.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 20 more minutes.
Cool. Fill with pudding, ice cream, etc.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Cover rinds with water and boil until clean.
Drain thoroughly.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spices wrapped in cheesecloth ball.
Boil until clean, stirring occasionally.
Pour over rinds. Each day for 9 days, drain syrup, bring to a boil and pour over rinds.
On the 10th day, put in jars and process.

title: sugar-free fruit ices
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Freeze in small electric ice cream freezer according to directions or pour into freezer container. Freeze until almost set.
Remove and beat until smooth.
Return to freezer.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place apple juice in saucepan, undiluted and bring to boil.
Combine next 4 ingredients in small bowl; add little apple juice.
Stir until blended in saucepan of juice.
Pour this mixture over apples; stir until all slices are coated.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes; reduce to 375° and bake until done.

title: turkey gumbo soup
directions: The day before you are going to make the soup, cook the broth.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until well blended.
Add crabmeat to mixture.
Add grated cheese and onion. Blend thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat olive oil in nonstick skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until soft.
Add garlic.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add raw rice.
Turn up heat and stir and cook until rice begins to become opaquely white and onion begins to brown.
Add tomato and cilantro.
Stir until combined with rice mixture.
Add beef broth. Turn up heat and cook until broth comes to a boil.
Cover.
Turn heat down to simmer and cook for about 20 minutes until rice is done.

title: three tier dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with flour and nuts.
Pat into a long glass dish.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool crust.

title: beef horseradish rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Spread on dried beef slices. Roll and chill until ready to serve.
You may slice in bite size pieces.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place chuck roast in roasting pan and add all of the above ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Add water, if necessary, to prevent scorching.
After roast is finished and cooled, pull apart and shred with fingers.
Remove fat, gristle and bone.
(I usually double the recipe and freeze half of it for future use. The recipe feeds eight hungry guests.)

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken in salty water.
Remove and cut into small pieces.
Rub with red pepper and garlic powder.
Put chicken in large casserole dish.
Cut a large onion into small pieces and grate Velveeta cheese.
Put over chicken.
Crush and sprinkle 1/2 package of taco Doritos over chicken mixture.
Blend mushroom and chicken soups with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour over chicken.
Put rest of Doritos on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook for
5 minutes.
Pour over 1 cup raw rice and bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate morsels.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, marshmallows and nuts; stir.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator to harden. Store in a cool place in sealed container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat cream cheese and soup in a saucepan until melted. Remove from heat and add gelatine. When cool, add rest of ingredients. Pour into bowl or mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: casserole pork chops
directions: Place rice in casserole or covered dish.
Arrange chops on top of rice.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Place a slice of onion, tomato and green pepper on each chop.
Pour boiling water to moisten rice.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain
asparagus
tips and place in well greased casserole. Cover with grated cheese.
Mix soup and milk well; pour over asparagus and cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°;
sprinkle onion rings over top and brown 10 minutes longer.

title: orange ball cookies
directions: Mix wafers, coconut and orange juice together.
Roll into balls and roll balls into confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate cookies afterwards.
Dough can be refrigerated before rolling in sugar, also, to help hold dough together better.

title: gooey butter squares
directions: Beat until creamy.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash and drain berries. Add vinegar. Let come to boil. Add sugar. Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until desired thickness. Stir occasionally while cooking and while cooling.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add pineapple, pie filling and pecans.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip until smooth and spread on top of Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: southern corn meal muffins
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mix.
Combine egg whites, yogurt and oil.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moist.
Spoon mixture into muffin pans coated with cooking spray. Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Chop ham fine.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together over boiling water.
Beat 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: enchilados
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place meat and cheese in tortillas and roll tight.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine the soup, sour cream and garlic salt. Add potatoes and cheddar cheese; mix well.

title: garlic and cheese biscuits
directions: Combine baking mix, milk and shredded cheese with wooden spoon until soft dough forms, then beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Combine butter or margarine (melted) and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from your cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and steak in shortening; add flour until smooth. Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours; add mushrooms and sour cream.
Heat until hot.
Serve over noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika.
Form into a ball.
Chill. Roll ball in paprika.
You can roll in pecans.

title: cinnamon twists(welcome school's)
directions: Roll biscuits to 7-inch lengths; dip in melted butter, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Fold in half.
Seal ends and twist! Place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Stir and mix well together.
Cook until thick.
Add small onion, grated.
Grate 1 pound of Cheddar cheese and mix all together.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Shake well.
Serve over your own slaw mixture.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Allow bread to thaw.
Stir together cinnamon and sugar.
Roll out dough to a rectangle 7 x 5-inches. Spread butter evenly over dough.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over dough.
Roll dough up, starting at narrow end.
Pinch to seal. Place seam down in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter. Add sugars.
Cream together. Add eggs and milk. Mix flour and soda.
Blend with first mixture. Place balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheets. Dip fork in water and make criss-cross patterns on top. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: beef soup (quick)
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until meat is no longer pink; drain off drippings.
Add barley, carrots, celery and tomatoes with liquid (chop up tomatoes).
Add beef consomme, water, tomato soup (if using), bay leaf, 1/4 cup parsley and salt and pepper as desired.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: quickie brownies
directions: Stir all ingredients together; spread into a shallow 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut when cool.
Glaze with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: berry smash
directions: Add sugar and vodka to the gallon jug of berries with a good lid.
Let stand for 3 months.
Drain and have some fun.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Reduce heat and simmer one hour.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add small amounts of dry ingredients and small amounts of milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake 80 minutes at 325°.

title: thai beef with broccoli
directions: Partially freeze round steak.
With a sharp knife, slice meat very thin and into bite-size pieces.
In blender container, combine water, garlic, 2 tablespoons cooking oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, red pepper, fish sauce and cornstarch.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Set aside.
Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat. Add 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Stir-fry broccoli, 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove broccoli from wok.
Add more oil, if necessary; add half of the beef strips.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes; remove and finish cooking rest of beef, then return all the beef and broccoli to wok.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cover and cook 1 minute more.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.
Serves 4.

title: homemade coconut cream pie
directions: Filling:
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir, over medium heat, until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Use a long baking dish.
Drain pineapple and mix with cheese. Mix sugars with flour and pour over pineapple and cheese mixture. Top with Ritz crackers.
Drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are browned and mixture is bubbly.

title: cabbage loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf baking pan.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
After 45 minutes, you may have to drain bacon grease.
During the last 15 minutes, add tomato paste on top.
Turn oven off.
After 15 minutes, add cheese slices to top and allow to melt.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda.
Bring butter, water and cocoa to a boil, then pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour in greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: malcolm's lemon mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in water; let dissolve (about 10 minutes) over low heat.
Cool slowly, stirring occasionally, so it does not get on the bottom or around the edges of the pan.
Beat eggs and sugar about 7 minutes at high speed until thick and light.
Whip 1 1/2 cups of heavy cream into peaks; refrigerate.
Add lemon rind and juice to cooked gelatin and stir.
Juice and gelatin must be at the same temperature to avoid gelled lumps.
Pour mixture into egg-sugar mixture; blend well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream until mixture is uniform.
Pour into a serving bowl by Malcolm Davis; chill 3 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped cream and strawberries.

title: vegetarian lasagna supreme
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add garlic, onion and vegetables and saute a few minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and herbs and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Mix flour and water and stir into sauce.
Simmer about 10 minutes longer, then remove bay leaf.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all ingredients, salt and pepper to taste and cook on medium for 1 hour.

title: cheese and olive balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Blend together cheese and butter using a mixer. Add flour and paprika. Mix thoroughly and shape 1 tablespoon of this mixture around each olive, dipping hands in flour to prevent sticking. Arrange on baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes just to a golden color. Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix in a bag and shake, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and cracker crumbs.
Dip chicken in butter.
Shake chicken in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cornbread stuffing
directions: *Or you may use all cornbread.
If you do, use 4 cups cornbread instead of 2.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spices and mix well.
Add cheese in small pieces and stir over medium heat until melted.
Place on party rye by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Clean and cut up fruit.
Blend low-fat cottage cheese and add to fruit.

title: steak rolls
directions: Salt and pepper steaks; place onions and bacon mixture on steak pieces.
Roll up and place a couple of toothpicks to hold together.
Place in Dutch oven sprayed with Pam with lid on and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook egg noodles.
Drain these, then add to steak rolls.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse in hot water, then cold water. Mix together remaining ingredients with macaroni and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugars and slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream butter and add half the sugar, gradually.
Beat egg with remaining sugar.
Combine mixtures.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Measure flour, wheat germ, baking soda and salt into a large bowl; stir to blend.
In a bowl of food processor, combine the eggs, bananas, honey, vegetable oil, lemon juice and vanilla until well blended.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add walnuts.
Stir with rubber spatula just until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until sides pull away from pan and pick inserted in center comes out clean (about 45 to 55 minutes).
Cool on rack before removing from pan.
Makes one 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together until smooth.
Bake in a well-greased loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour, then at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter and milk.
Add Bisquick.
Make into balls and roll into granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Be careful not to overbake.
They harden quickly.
Press a chocolate Kiss in each cookie immediately after removing from oven.

title: betty's hawaiian ribs
directions: Brown ribs in heavy frypan or Dutch oven.
Combine cornstarch, molasses and soy sauce to make paste. Spread paste on both sides of ribs. Re-brown quickly in hot fat.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water and pineapple juice. Heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and cook 25 to 30 minutes. Add pinapple chunks and green pepper cubes.
Re-cover. Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Measure milk in a saucepan (set aside). Separate egg yolks from whites (set whites aside). Beat yolks. Combine flour, cocoa and sugar; mix well. Heat milk over medium heat until warm; add yolks. Then add cocoa mixture. Cook until this thickens. Remove from stove. Add vanilla and butter. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue of your choice.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter together.
Press this mixture into the 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs together.
Spread over mixture in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lowell inn crescent rolls
directions: Put 1/4 cup of warm water (not hot) in a cup.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar and 1/8 teaspoon ginger.
Add 2 packages of yeast.
Let this stand until bubbly.
Cream together 1/2 cup shortening or 1 stick butter or margarine, 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 well beaten eggs, then add 1 teaspoon salt and 3/4 cup warm water and yeast mixture. Stir well.
Add 2 cups of bread flour and 2 cups plain flour.
Beat this mixture.
Knead 6 minutes in a mixer (or by hand).
The dough will be smooth and elastic.
Put dough in large bowl and place in warm place.
Put a little oil on top of dough.
Cover with wax paper, then with a light towel until the dough doubles in size. Roll out on a dough board into a 12 to 15-inch circle.
Take a sharp knife, dipped in flour and half the dough.
Cut into halves again until you have 16 pizza shaped pieces.
Roll into crescent rolls, beginning with the bigger end.
Dip each roll in warm butter.
Let rise to double size, then bake at 350° until done. Brush with butter when rolls are done.

title: cajun party mix(as advertised by durkee)
directions: Melt butter in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire and cheese.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix very well.
Bake on large, uncovered baking sheet for 45 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Cut cream cheese in small pieces; mix well.
I use a wire whip to mix cream cheese. Mix in pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator to gel.

title: best ever caramels
directions: Mix together in heavy pan all ingredients except vanilla and nuts. Cook slowly over medium heat, stirring.
Cook to 250°
or firm ball. Remove from heat. Add the vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. When firm, turn out on cutting board and cut into bite size pieces.
Wrap in wax paper squares.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Mix the nuts and coconut and place in bottom of pan.
Mix the cake mix as directed on box and pour over first layer.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spoon on top of the chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in large saucepan.
Place over medium heat.
Stir until sugar has dissolved.
Place lid on pan and turn up heat.
When crystals of sugar have dissolved from sides of pan, remove lid.
Cook until mixture comes to a hard boil.
Add peanuts.
Stir constantly until it reaches hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat; add soda.
Stir 2 or 3 minutes and pour into large cookie sheet.
Spread very thin.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix the flour with the sugar before you mix with eggs.
Put in two (9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: cheese-ham strata
directions: Tear bread into chunks.
Place half of the pieces in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese and ham over bread.
Place rest of bread over cheese and ham.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard.
Stir well.
Pour over bread, ham and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: mama hull's christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix together soda and syrup and add. Add nutmeg, cloves, allspice and cinnamon.
Mix.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Add flour and buttermilk, alternating each.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Watch cake.

title: asparagus-feta hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut crusts off bread and roll with a rolling pin to flatten. Cut in half lengthwise.
Spread an even layer of mayonnaise on each piece.
Sprinkle Feta cheese over mayonnaise.
Cut asparagus to size of width of bread.
Place at one end of bread and roll up. Bake at 375° until golden on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Serve hot.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Melt Hershey bars and mix with syrup and add vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients to oleo and sugar mixture, alternately with chocolate mixture and buttermilk.
Bake in a tube cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.
It may require 15 to 25 minutes longer.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake as directed on box.
Fold in orange peel.
Bake as directed.
Toss berries with the cup of sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Beat whipping cream with the 1/4 cup of sugar in a chilled bowl until stiffened.
Cut the cake in slices. Top each slice with the strawberry and cream mixture.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt the butter and saute the green onions and parsley.
Blend in flour slowly and smooth out with 1 pint of cream (or canned milk).
Add Swiss cheese and stir until melted and smooth.
Gently put in 1 pound crabmeat and salt and peppers to taste.
Add sherry and simmer 7 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine 1 cup of the flour and the fructose, Stevia Rebaudiana, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add banana, shortening and milk.
Then add remaining flour. Beat until well blended (at least 2 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Transfer batter to a well-greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until pick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Remove from oven and allow to cool in pan for 10 minutes. Transfer to cooling rack.
This bread is best the second day.

title: meat stew
directions: We get a pot and get popcorn.
Then we get water.
Then we get celery and get the crust.
First we get a can of soup.
Then we get a bag of popcorn.
Then we pop the popcorn.
We get a pot and put in some bouillon cubes.
Then we pop the popcorn.
Then we put butter in the popcorn and put it all in the pot.
Cook it for 10 hours.
Scoop it into bowls and eat.

title: oriental meat loaf
directions: Blend together all ingredients; pack lightly in pan.
Bake at 350°.
Serve with soy sauce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mash bananas in electric mixer.
Add all remaining ingredients, including the bananas, to the creamed mixture.
Mix well and pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans (3 x 7-inch).
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 to 60 minutes, depending on oven.
Cool on cookie racks.
(Okinawa 1971.)

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all together.
Heat in oven or microwave until butter is melted.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: elephant stew
directions: Blend all ingredients well in large pot over medium heat. Season to taste.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
If stew seems to lack flavor, one or two small hares may be added; however, be frugal with the hares, because some people can become very offended when they find a hare in their stew.

title: marble squares
directions: In a small mixing bowl combine flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl with electric mixer cream together butter, sugars, eggs, vanilla and water.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in by hand 1 1/2 cups of chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9-inch by 9-inch by 2-inch baking pan and sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of chocolate chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and run a knife through the top layer of chocolate chips and bake 1 more minute.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix and spread on dough all other ingredients.
Sprinkle with fresh vegetables, chopped broccoli, onion, carrots, red and green pepper.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: mushroom and sausage pie
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add mushrooms; cook over high heat, stirring frequently, until mushrooms and meat are lightly browned and all liquid from mushrooms has evaporated. Drain off any excess grease.
Stir in parsley.
Beat eggs with half and half and Parmesan cheese.
Blend in mushroom mixture and salt. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Arrange mushrooms so that any stems are turned down in liquid.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until crust is well browned and filling is set.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and separate from bone into bite-size pieces. Layer bottom of baking pan with crackers.
Combine chicken, sour cream and soup.
Pour over crackers.
Layer top with crackers and cover entirely with poppy seed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash pickles
directions: Layer squash, onions and bell peppers.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Drain off excess liquid.
Heat other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Spoon into jars and seal.
Cool; chill at least 24 hours before serving.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Chop vegetables into 3/4-inch pieces.
Cook in 1 cup pickling salt with water to cover until tender.
Drain.
Using the same kettle in which vegetables were cooked, cook remaining ingredients until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Add drained vegetables and bring to a boil again.
Immediately put in hot jars and process accordingly.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and lemon peel.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter or oleo until well blended.
Stir in egg and nuts.
Reserve half the dough for topping.
With floured hand, pat other half of dough into prepared pan.
Spread preserves to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Crumble reserved dough as topping over preserves.
Bake 45 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Store covered up to 3 days or wrap and freeze.

title: easy baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Place in a buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken with spanish rice
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, warm the oil. Sprinkle both sides of the chicken with the paprika.
Add the chicken to the skillet and cook until golden on both sides, 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove the chicken to a dish and cover loosely to keep warm.

title: wonderful meat marinade
directions: Whisk ingredients together.
Pour over meat and marinate 2 hours to overnight in refrigerator.
Use leftover to baste meat while it cooks.

title: chicken, rice, and broccoli dish
directions: Cook rice, broccoli and cheese mix according to pkg. directions. Cook chopped broccoli, drain off water and add rice mixture. Melt 1/4 cup marg. and pour over rice and broccoli mixture. Rinse chicken breast tenders and cook till done in a skillet. Cut into small cubes and add to above mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and place in 325 degree oven for 25-30 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on chili.
Then add grated cheese on top. Heat until hot and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and 1 cup pecans.
Spread in 9
x 13 inch dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust. Mix pudding with milk,
stirring until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans on top.
Chill.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Cut
bread
lengthwise.
Place on cookie sheet.
Spread with butter.
Sprinkle
on garlic powder, Romano and Parmesan cheese and
a
small
amount
of
oregano if desired.
Spread shredded Mozzarella evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal cookies with coconut
directions: Mix all ingredients, starting with butter, sugar and egg, then remainder in order.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased sheets.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add oatmeal, syrup and vanilla.
Then press in 11 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Then melt together chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread over top of first mixture.
Cool; cut in bars and remove from pan.
Refrigerate.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Mix together remaining ingredients and boil.
Pour over the dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: curried shrimp and crab sauce (over pasta)
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add garlic, onion and parsley and cook until onion is tender, about 4 minutes.
Stir in curry powder.
Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Stir about 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook at a gentle boil until sauce thickens slightly.

title: granola
directions: *Can substitute any type of flakes for dates.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Crumble bread and soak in milk; add beaten egg.
Mix with other ingredients, except tomato juice.
Shape into 8 balls and place in greased casserole dish.
Pour tomato juice over the balls and bake at 350° oven (preheat).

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly and remove 1 cup for topping.
Mix remaining ingredients in another bowl and add to dry mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
To make topping, add 2 tablespoons of brown sugar and 2 to 3 teaspoons cinnamon to 1 cup dry mixture left.
Pour on topping and press in with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in a deep bowl in order given.
Spread mayonnaise over top, completely covering cheese layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with several layers of plastic wrap to seal.
Let sit 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: kahlua-pecan brie
directions: Remove rind from top of cheese, cutting to within 1/2 inch of outside edges.
Place on an ovensafe dish.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased casserole at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand to develop flavors. Serve with raw vegetables, potato chips or crackers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Trim crust from as many slices of bread as will fit in bottom of dish.
Saute the sausage; crumble and drain well.
Put sausage on top of bread.
Saute green pepper and onion; drain well and spoon over sausage.
Layer cheese over vegetables.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper; pour over cheese.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
May leave in refrigerator overnight before baking or may freeze now.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: supreme potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with peeling, then peel and dice after cooling. Add rest of ingredients; top with corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zippy cranberry cooler
directions: Combine 1 pint bottle cranberry juice cocktail, chilled with frozen lemonade concentrate and 2 cups cold water.
Just before serving, add ice cubes.
Carefully pour two bottles of lemon-lime carbonated soda, chilled, down side of pitcher.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: divinity
directions: Heat sugar, syrup and water in a two quart sauce pan over low heat.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 260° on a candy thermometer or until soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, continue beating while pouring syrup in a thin stream into egg whites, add vanilla, beat until mixture holds shape and becomes slightly dull.
Drop mix from a buttered spoon on waxed paper. Put nut on top of each drop if desired.

title: lowell inn crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients except half of flour.
Add rest of flour and mix until smooth. Scrape dough from sides and cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double (1 1/2 hours).
Divide in half.
Shape as butterhorns or crescents; roll out dough about 1/4-inch thick into 12-inch circle.
Spread the dough with soft butter.
Cut into 16 pie-shaped pieces.
Beginning at rounded edge, roll up.
Pull rounded edge out as you roll so the crescent will be long, instead of short and fat.
Place on pan, point underneath.
Cover; let rise until double, 1 hour.
Brush with butter.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until rich, golden brown.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and frost as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: frankfurter chowder
directions: Cook and stir margarine, franks, green pepper and onion over medium heat until brown.
Stir in corn and pepper sauce; heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together; drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cheddar cheese fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer. Put into a buttered 9 x 13 pan. Chill. Keep refrigerated.

title: hamburger and rice deluxe
directions: Brown hamburger in cast-iron skillet until tender. Add 1 cup water, salt, pepper, onion salt and sauce; simmer over low heat until boiling. Add rice and cover. Cook approximately 3 to 5 minutes; add remaining water. Cover and let rice steam, stirring occasionally. Rice may need more water. After rice is done, stir well and serve with hot vegetables. Yield: 5 servings.

title: marinated vegetable rice salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Combine all vegetables and rice in large container.
In saucepan, combine water, oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Heat almost to boiling and pour over rice and vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half.
Core and wash.
Drop into boiling water for about 1 minute.
Set aside to drain.
Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion.
Cook on low heat until onion is soft.
Drain grease, if necessary.
Add Spanish rice mix to hamburger mixture and salt and pepper to taste.
When mixture is thoroughly heated, fill each half of green pepper with mixture and top with 1/2 slice American cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is hot and bubbly.
Serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: bean stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stem from pepper; remove seeds and cut split in bottom. In a bowl, combine beans, cheese, raisins, salsa and chili powder. Stuff peppers with bean mixture.
Place in an ovenproof dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until peppers are soft and cheese has melted.

title: millionaire pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, margarine, vanilla and cream cheese. Pour into pie shells.

title: green rice
directions: Combine rice, water, salt and oleo and cook in tightly covered saucepan over low heat for 30 minutes without removing cover.
Add parsley and almonds and toss lightly with a fork.
Good with chicken or roast gravy.
Serves 8.

title: mama's applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheddar cheese and olive balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grate cheese and soften to room temperature.
Combine cheese, butter and paprika.
Mix well into flour, by hand, until pieces of cheese disappear and mixture is smooth and deep yellow in color.
Cover; allow to stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Pinch off small piece dough (1 teaspoon) and flatten in palm of hand to a circle.
Place well drained olive in dough; cover completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; chill 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve hot.
May be made in advance and frozen.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Do not thaw.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until browned; drain.
Add cumin, garlic, chili powder, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered, until most of liquid is gone.
Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put 1/2 of tortillas.
Spoon 1/2 cup taco sauce on tortillas.
Spoon on 1/2 of the beef mix. Top with sour cream and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil.
Can be refrigerated up to 24 hours at this point.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cheese and carrot scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots until tender.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onions until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in milk and mix the next 4 ingredients.
Cook until mixture becomes thick.
In another saucepan, melt butter and add bread crumbs.
Lightly grease casserole pan; add carrots, then cheese.
Repeat; at the end, top with bread crumbs.
Bake.

title: ginger haying tea
directions: Stir well.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together day ahead and store in Tupperware bowl.
Cook almonds and sugar on low for 30 minutes to coat nuts.
Add bacon and nuts just before serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and let stand 2 hours before serving with fresh vegetable.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and let set for 20 minutes the cranberries, apples, pineapple, pecans and juice.

title: aunt nova's cheese soup
directions: Cook together the first 7 ingredients until tender (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Combine milk with flour and add to vegetables.
Beat together.
Add cheese to vegetables and heat until cheese is melted.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Heat good and hot before serving.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and sift twice.
Add milk and melted butter and mix well.
Beat eggs thoroughly until light and mix into smooth batter that will pour easily.

title: little dumplings
directions: Mix egg with flour, salt and oil.
Meanwhile, heat broth. Spoon mixture into boiling broth using 1/4 teaspoon at a time.
Cook in broth for 2 or 3 minutes before serving.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together until dissolved.
Mix with 4 cucumbers, peeled and sliced thinly.
Let stand overnight.

title: walnut horns
directions: Combine all the ingredients except powdered sugar and mix until the mixture is smooth.
Put dough into freezer for about 30 minutes.
Take 1 tablespoon of dough at a time and roll it in your hands.
Put on a greased baking sheet and shape into a horn or crescent.
Bake horns at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and while they are still warm, coat with powdered sugar.

title: gone-all-afternoon stew
directions: Put beef, carrots, onions, potatoes, tomato soup, water, salt, pepper, basil and red cooking wine in lightly greased 3-quart casserole dish with a lid that fits tightly.
Stir ingredients. Cover tightly.
Bake in a preheated 275° oven for 4 hours (or a 250° oven 5 hours).
Add peas last 15 minutes.

title: hot dip
directions: Top with black olives and green onions after you have heated in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Quick and easy.

title: bart's butterfingers
directions: *Or use vanilla flavoring with 2 tablespoons of butterscotch topping.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Cube chicken and cook with bell pepper and onion.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to directions.
Pour sauce over chicken mixture and cook about 30 more minutes.
Serve over hot spaghetti noodles.

title: snowball
directions: Line mixing bowl with waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix together boiling water, orange juice, sugar and lemon juice and heat over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator until consistency of egg whites.
Fold in 1 pint Cool Whip. Layer cake pieces and gelatin mixture in lined bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold onto plate. Remove wrap and ice with remaining 1 pint Cool Whip.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt
the margarine or butter.
Add sugar.
Mix together, then
add
eggs
and
beat good.
Keep beating as you add flour and cocoa.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheeze-sausage appetizers
directions: Cook and drain sausage and turkey.
Melt cheese in mixture. Spread on cocktail bread (rye, etc.).
Broil until golden brown (about 2 minutes).
Can be frozen before broiling.

title: cobbler
directions: Sift into baking dish first 3 ingredients.
Add milk and stir with wooden spoon until smooth.
Melt butter and drizzle over batter.
Heat fruit (peaches, blueberries, blackberries, etc.) to boiling point and spoon over batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown on top.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, and sugar.
Add eggs, wine, spices and flavorings.
Mix fruit with 3 cups flour.
Add mixture to fruit. Drop and bake 20 minutes on 300° to 325°.

title: cheddar scallion soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet. Coarsely chop scallions.
In a food processor, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and pepper.
Add butter and process for 5 to 10 seconds or until mixture is crumbly and resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add scallions and cheddar and pulse briefly just to combine.
Add buttermilk and pulse just until dough forms a cohesive mass.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead for 30 seconds.
Form dough into round dome loaf about 5 inches in diameter.
Place loaf in baking sheet.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until top is brown.

title: baked chicken souffle
directions: Line 1 large baking dish with bread slices; top with chicken. Cook fresh mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes and spoon over chicken.
You may use canned mushrooms.
Next, spread over water chestnuts.
Dot with mayonnaise; top with cheese slices.
Mix eggs, milk and salt and pour over the cheese slices.
Mix soups and pimentos and spoon over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over top; bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
This is my favorite souffle!
Serves 12. Also freezes well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas real well.
Blend in butter, eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add flour and nuts; mix until well blended.
Pour in loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Heat sugar, honey and oleo together until sugar is melted. Baste raw chicken pieces and place in slow cooker for 1 hour on low heat, then place on barbecue grill to brown.
Baste again.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix melted margarine and onion together until onion is lightly brown. Add dressing and mix well.
Spread half of dressing in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add dressing and mix well.
Add cut up chicken. Mix chicken broth with cream of chicken soup.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Add the other half of dressing and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot cheese and ham croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Open croissant cartons and separate dough.
Spread each with a little mustard, a piece of ham, trimmed to correct size and sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll each croissant from the broad end towards the point and shape to a crescent. Place on cookie sheet and brush with glaze.
Bake in center of oven for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix together chicken, stuffing, soups and broth.
Melt butter in Pyrex casserole dish.
Pour mixture in dish and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Shape ground beef into 4 patties.
Place in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until about 3/4 done.
Drain on paper towel really well.
Place patties in baking dish. Combine brown gravy mix, water, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Pour over patties.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Uncover and leave in oven for an additional 5 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange one layer of bread slices in 2-inch deep greased baking pan or dish, cover with cheese.
Top with another layer of bread. Beat eggs, add milk, mustard, onion, salt and pepper together and mix.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate one hour or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° about 50 minutes or until fluffy and brown.
Serves about 35.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add to prepared pie crust.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until center is set.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: stir-fried beef and broccoli
directions: For the Rice: Put 2 cups of water and 1 cup of long cooking rice in pan.
Turn burner on medium heat.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook for about 12 minutes, or until water has evaporated and rice is sticky.
Remove from heat and leave covered until serving.

title: angel hair pasta with lemon and garlic
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat and maintain at a boil.
Put the olive oil and garlic in a saucepan and cook over medium heat just until the garlic begins to brown. Remove the saute pan from the heat and pour in the wine.
Return it to the heat.
Cook for another 1 to 2 minutes, until the wine has been reduced by half.
Stir in the lemon juice and tomato.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Place the pasta in the boiling water and cook to desired doneness, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Drain the pasta and put it into a warm serving bowl.
Add the basil, Parmesan cheese and black pepper along with the tomato mixture.
Toss and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: bananas foster
directions: Mix butter and sugar in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until caramelized.
Cut bananas in quarters.
Add and cook until tender. Add cinnamon and liquor; stir.
Add rum to top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Light.
