Spoon over vanilla ice cream while flaming. Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In large skillet brown beef, drain.
Add onion, pepper, pepperoni, and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add pasta and sauce; heat thoroughly.
Put in 9 by 13 inch pan.
Top with cheese, and bake at 350° for 15 minutes until cheese melts.
Pasta can be macaroni, wheels or your choice.

title: crispy herb baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease or line with foil 15 x 1-inch pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt; stir until well mixed.
Dip chicken pieces into margarine.
Roll in potato flakes mixture to coat.
Place in pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Fix the day before:
Cook chicken breasts with a little butter, Accent and salt until tender.
Cut in pieces; mix well all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Put in large 13 x 9-inch heatproof dish.
Put on top the next day the grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: rosie's unfried chicken
directions: Put cut pieces of chicken in ice water for 1/2 hour.
Mix last 10 ingredients listed for breading.
Take chicken out of ice water, dip in yogurt and then in breading.
Place in a pan which has been sprayed with light cooking spray.
Spray each piece of chicken to prevent drying.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° turning every 20 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until frothy.
Add chunks of butter (about 4 tablespoons), half and half and cracker crumbs.
(Reserve small amount for top.)
Add corn and liquid; stir well.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with reserved crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chewy granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13 pan.
Combine oats, flour, soda, vanilla, butter, honey and brown sugar in large mixing bowl.
Stir in the 2 cups of your choice of chips, nuts or fruit.
Firmly press into the prepared pan and bake for 20 to 22 minutes.
If you overbake it, they will be too crumbly, so watch when the edges and top start to brown and take out to cool.
Let cool 10 minutes and then cut bars.
Then let cool completely before removing bars.

title: oven dried jerky
directions: Trim and discard all fat from meat.
Cut meat into 1/4-inch strips and cut across grain.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Stir and dissolve as much as possible.
Add meat.
Mix thoroughly and coat meat well.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Cover center of oven racks with aluminum foil.
Arrange meat strips on oven racks.
Dry at lowest temperature until hard (4 to 7 hours) or overnight, depending on thickness of meat.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it boils and the sugar melts completely.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes.
Place on wax paper with teaspoon. (I roll it into balls with my hands, dipping hands in cold water occasionally.)

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour and water into a ball.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Put in chicken broth and add cool chicken.
Let cook for 25 minutes on low.
Cover until served.

title: layered-taco dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and drain fat.
Add chilies and bouillon.
Cook.
Stir until bouillon dissolves.
Cool.

title: lemon-rosemary marinade
directions: Pour hot water over rosemary and let cool. Stir in all remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. It is very strong. Does not take much to marinate.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour (as for biscuits).
Stir in milk. Pat dough out into about 1/4-inch thick rectangle on a piece of floured waxed paper.
Spread uncooked sausage evenly onto dough. Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut into slices and bake on ungreased pan at 425° until brown.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Add softened cream cheese and mix well until blended.
Spread into graham cracker pie crust.
Top with cherry pie filling or your favorite filling.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix next 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Mash bananas, milk and lemon juice together and mix with first and second bowl until smooth.
Pour into 2 pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cajun chow mein
directions: Grease Dutch oven.
Mix all ingredients.
Use hands to mix well.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Since the canned soups are undiluted and the seasoning in these are sufficient, adding salt and pepper are optional.

title: salami roll-ups
directions: Take a piece of salami and spread some softened cream cheese over the top part of the salami. Add a piece of green onion. Roll into a tight roll. This is a great appetizer.

title: salmon cheddar quiche
directions: Add all ingredients to a 9-inch deep dish pie shell (unbaked) or a 10-inch regular pie shell (unbaked).
Just before placing in the oven, mix eggs and milk together and pour over salmon ingredients.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Blend all and pour into 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with green onions and bacon or buttered cornflakes.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: "gingerbeard" bears
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate dough; then roll out and cut with cookie cutters (preferably bear-shaped ones). Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef patties parmesan
directions: Combine beef, Bisquick, green pepper, egg, garlic and seasonings.
Shape into patties in greased shallow baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle each patty with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: saucepan cocoa brownies
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan over medium heat.
When melted, take off burner and add sugar; mix.
Add cocoa; mix well.
Add eggs; mix. Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Add syrup.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased cookie sheet (for thinner brownies) or in a 9
x 13-inch pan (for thicker brownies) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and oil to boiling point and pour over vegetables, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator or for as long as 2 weeks.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Mix in flour, paprika and salt. Shape about 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
When ready to serve, unwrap desired number.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 30.

title: gyoza(japan)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put small amount (full teaspoon) on won ton.
Water edges and pinch together.
Fry until golden brown in oil.
Dip in soy sauce or mustard mix.
Very good.

title: plantation cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with cake mix, then add sour cream, eggs and oil. Stir only with a fork.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: nine-bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in large stockpot with enough water to cover by 2 inches.
Let soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham bone, onion, garlic and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, basil, oregano and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes longer.
Remove ham bone and bay leaves.
Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 to 8 minutes, drain well.
Combine with broccoli the remaining ingredients except crackers and place in medium casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crackers. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in pan and bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add coconut or nuts and stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set for 20 minutes.

title: bisquick pineapple cookies
directions: Bake in 375° oven 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.

title: sugar cutout cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients (baking powder, baking soda, salt and flour). Refrigerate overnight.

title: raisin-cheese pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and blend well.
Add raisins and water.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add salt, margarine, grated orange rind and juice from the orange, Angostura aromatic Bitters and lemon juice.
Cool filling, then pour into 8-inch uncooked pastry shell.
Arrange the cheese slices or grated cheese over the filling and cover with top crust.
Seal and crimp edges of pie.
Bake in a hot oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Should be nicely browned. Serves 6.

title: baked ham slice sauterne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ham in a shallow baking pan; set aside.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; stir in water and margarine.
Place over medium-high heat and cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and stir in raisins and wine.
Pour the mixture over ham.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kielbasa cabbage soup
directions: In soup kettle, saute cabbage, onion and garlic in oil for 5-10 minutes or until tender.
Combine water, vinegar and brown sugar, add to cabbage mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 60-70 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield:
8-10 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix juice and cornstarch in a pan; cook over medium heat until clear.
Add sugar and butter.
Stir until melted.
Add pineapple. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: gazpacho(from jane brody - good food gourmet)
directions: Put the cucumber, green pepper, red pepper, celery, carrot and onion in the bowl of a food processor and chop them.
Do not drain the liquid.
In a large serving bowl, combine the tomato juice with the remaining ingredients.
Mix in the chopped vegetables and their juices.
Chill the gazpacho for at least 1 hour before serving it. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cuban steak
directions: Cover
meat
with
garlic
salt and chopped onion.
Let stand approximately
1 hour.
Remove onion and save.
Place 1 slice sandwich
ham
and	1/4
hard-boiled egg in each steak. Roll
and pin.
Sear in oil.	Cover with tomato sauce and add chopped onions.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours or until done, or 20 minutes in a pressure cooker.
Serves 4.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate, water and shortening in top of double boiler until chocolate is melted and the mixture is glossy when beaten slightly.
(This can be done in the microwave.)
Remove from heat and place in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
(This batter is very thin; do not add more flour.)
Pour batter into greased pans and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch layers or a 9 x 13-inch pan (bake this 40 to 45 minutes).

title: broiled sourdough slices
directions: Preheat broiler.
Slice French bread.
Blend remaining ingredients and spread evenly over bread slices.
Broil until golden and bubbly.

title: layered salad(in clear bowl)
directions: Add lettuce, onion, water chestnuts or almonds, cauliflower, peas, mayonnaise and sugar.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Before serving, add crumpled bacon, chopped eggs, salt, pepper and tomato wedges.
Serve.

title: mexican hot dogs
directions: Warm tortillas and melt 2 slices of cheese on each.
Place hot dog inside and roll closed.
Add some fruit and vegetable for complete lunch.

title: baked pita chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine olive oil, garlic, mustard, lemon juice and basil in a small bowl.
Split the pitas in half horizontally.
Using a pastry brush, dampened with water, brush the cut sides of each piece of pita with the oil mixture.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar, butter, flour, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour into pan first.
Boil cherries, water and sugar.
Pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oat & raisin cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into creamed mixture.
Add oats, raisins and sesame seeds.
Mix well.
Place by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with back of spoon. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool on cookie sheet slightly. Then move to rack.
Makes 10.

title: armadillo eggs no. 1
directions: Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Seed and devein jalapenos, using gloves to protect hands.
Stuff peppers with cheese.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares and store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: tender salad
directions: For vinaigrette, whisk together olive oil (reserve 1 tablespoon for later), orange juice, ginger, garlic, curry powder, seasoned salt, vinegar, and brown sugar.
Rinse chicken; pat dry. Place chicken and 1/2 cup vinaigrette in plastic food bag; marinate in refrigerator for several hours.
Discard marinade.
In separate food bag, combine sweet potatoes, apples, and 1/2 cup vinaigrette. Let stand for several hours.
Reserve remaining vinaigrette to dress the salad.

title: overnight anti-pasta salad
directions: Add to marinated vegetables.
Mix and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and bell pepper; drain. Crumble Doritos evenly into casserole dish.
Combine Ro-Tel, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom.
Pour onto Doritos.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top and cook at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well the first five ingredients.
*One cup nuts can be added.
I put nuts on top and also sliced bananas.

title: poppy seed bread and orange glaze
directions: Beat together
eggs,
sugar,
oil and milk.
Add flour, baking powder,
salt, poppy seed and extract.
Put batter into 8 1/2 x
4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool bread 10 minutes.
Remove from tin.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine thoroughly all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
You can use plums or apricots.

title: hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix hash browns, sour cream, cheese, soup, onions and melted butter together.
Put in a 9 x 13 casserole.
Mix crumbs and butter and pour over the top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: old man kelsey's deer jerky
directions: Trim all fat from the meat.
Slice the meat as thinly as possible.
In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the meat and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shake the excess liquid from the meat and arrange in a shallow pan or cookie sheet.
Dry the meat in a 150° to 200° oven until dry and brown,
a minimum of 8 hours.
Cool; remove from the pan and store in a glass jar.
If spicy hot jerky is desired, you may sprinkle coarsely ground black pepper over the meat just before placing it in the oven.

title: crab meat quickie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the last two.
Pat the bottom of pie shell with little dabs of butter before putting in ingredients.
Pour ingredients into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook
ground
beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add tomato soup, tomato paste, tomato sauce, cream of chicken soup and
Cheez Whiz.
Cook
until cheese is melted.
Cook noodles according to package
directions.
In baking dish, layer first the ground beef mixture, then
a
layer
of
noodles,
then
a second layer of the beef mixture.
Cook
at
350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Saute onion, olive oil and garlic together until onions are soft.
Cut cooked chicken into bite sized pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for about an hour on stovetop or put in slow cooker for about 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with sour cream, shredded jalapeno and Monterey jack cheese and tortilla chips.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish 1 thick layer of onions and 1 layer of sliced potatoes.
Over this, pour 1 can kidney beans with juice included.
Add hamburger meat or steak patties.
Salt each layer. Spread 1 can tomato soup over entire mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are tender.

title: cracker cake
directions: Crush crackers finely. Add beaten egg whites.
Add sugar and pecans.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool. Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: red top chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
The longer you cook, the better the taste!

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into sandwiches.

title: garden vegetable spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill at least 1 hour.
Serve on party bread or celery stalks.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Combine yellow cake mix, butter and 1 egg in a
large
bowl;
mix well.
Pat down into an even layer in a 13 x
9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat cream cheese in a medium size bowl
until fluffy; beat in the remaining 3 eggs and
almond extract.
Stir
in	sugar
until
smooth.
Spread cheese mixture over
cake mixture in pan.	Bake for 50 minutes or until a wooden pick
inserted
in center of cake comes out clean.	Cool in pan on wire rack.	Cut in rectangles to serve. (Cake will sink in middle.)

title: crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix breadcrumbs, eggs, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Fry in hot fat (350°) until browned or pan-fry in little butter or oil until browned on both sides.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: In a bowl, combine mix and milk.
(If too sticky, add more Bisquick.)
Roll out like pie dough to 1/4-inch thick.
(Keep as square as possible.)
Crumble up sausage on dough.
(Cover well.) Mash sausage into dough with fork.
Roll up like jelly roll. Seal edges well with wet fork.
Cut roll with bread knife into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Take out and cool. Ready to eat.
Makes 24.
Can be frozen.

title: strawberry layer cake
directions: Empty cake mix and jello in mixing bowl; add oil and eggs. Beat 3 minutes in mixer; add strawberries.
(If frozen berries, drain off liquid.)
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into 3 oiled cake pans. Bake 25 minutes at 350° or 375°.
Cool before icing.

title: ratatouille nicoise
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cube zucchini.
Cook eggplant and zucchini 10 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Chop tomatoes.
Chop onion and brown in oil.
Add eggplant, zucchini, tomatoes, crushed garlic, parsley, bay leaf and salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes. Place in shallow baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Brown in oven.
Serve with French bread.

title: mango fruit parfait
directions: Puree mangos and orange juice.
Slice 20 strawberries (leave 4 whole).
Line bottom of 4 balloon wine glasses with sliced strawberries.
Pour a thin layer of puree over each to cover. Reserve 4 kiwi slices.
Layer rest on top of puree.
Divide remainder of puree among glasses.
Top each with slice of kiwi surrounded by raspberries.
Make a slit in each of whole strawberries and position on rim of each glass.
Serves 4. Contains 139 calories and 0.8 g.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Mix ingredients well and knead.
Roll out with rolling pin. Cut crisscross, like diamonds, with a knife and bake in oven.

title: gumdrop bread
directions: Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook all ingredients, except topping, until thick, stirring constantly.
After cool, mix in topping.
Makes 1 pie.

title: selma's butter
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature (very important). Place ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat slow to mix.
Beat on high until fluffy (15 to 20 minutes).
Tastes like home churned butter. Can be frozen.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, melt butter in oven and remove.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add cheese and thawed, drained spinach and mix.
Pour in baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes.
Cut into bite-size squares.

title: bacon stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Rub with butter and bake.
Cut oval in top of	each
potato.
Scoop out into bowl.
Add butter, sour cream, egg, salt, pepper and bacon.
Refill potatoes, mounding high. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: texas hot sauce
directions: Fry onion and hamburger in large saucepan until meat is in fine pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 2 hours.

title: mary's sauerkraut and tomato casserole
directions: Cook sauerkraut until juice is evaporated. Add tomatoes and brown sugar. Stir well. Pour into casserole. Add melted oleo to bread crumbs. Put crumbs on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are browned. May add wieners or smoked sausage cut into pieces if desired.

title: mocha praline cookies
directions: Combine and bring to boil the milk, coffee and sugar.
Remove from heat, add water and margarine.
Stir until melted.
Add eggs, salt, maple and vanilla flavoring; beat well.
Slowly add coffee mixture, stirring constantly.
Then add flour and pecans.
Mix well.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then the dry ingredients.
Chill
dough for 1 hour.
Roll out; cut cookies and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add Crisco oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into three 1 pound coffee cans, greased and floured well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oreo cookie ice cream pie
directions: Mix crushed Oreos and melted butter; press onto bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over crust, then spread Spanish peanuts (with skins) over ice cream and then spread melted chocolate chips over peanuts.
Freeze several hours before serving.

title: sheepherder's breakfast
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp. Drain all but 1/2 cup of the drippings.
Add hash browns to skillet; mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, turning when browned.
Make 10 "wells" evenly spaced in the hash browns. Place one egg in each "well."
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Sprinkle cheese if desired.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes or until eggs are set.
Garnish with parsley; serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.
This casserole dish is especially good for breakfast when camping.
Served with toast, juice, milk or coffee is a big hit with the breakfast crowd.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine sugar with eggs, oil, sour cream and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in flour mixture.
Fold in apple and nuts; pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheese soup
directions: Stir until well mixed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When reheating, use low heat as it burns easily.

title: layered banana-pineapple dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange bananas on crust.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes and beat until blended.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: May add more potatoes and carrots.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain
salmon
and
remove skin and bone.
Flake salmon with fork and add cream cheese, lemon juice, onions, salt and liquid smoke.
Stir well.	Chill mixture overnight or several hours. Shape
into
2 nice logs or 1 large log.
Combine nuts and parsley.
Stir
well and roll the salmon log in the pecan mixture and chill several hours.
This freezes well.

title: chile con queso
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients except for cheese and simmer for 30 minutes.
Melt in cheese.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, Accent, sugar, salt and pepper a day ahead; refrigerate.
Combine chicken, lettuce, onion, cilantro and cashews; pour dressings over salad just before serving.
Serve over rice sticks.
Makes 15 to 20 small salads or 10 to 12 entree salads.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape in rolls; chill thoroughly. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fluffy rolls
directions: Cream and blend together shortening and sugar, then add one cup boiling water and let cool.
Then add eggs.
Dissolve yeast into 1 cup lukewarm water and add to mixture.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add 4 cups to the mixture and blend thoroughly until the dough is smooth.
Gradually add the balance of the flour. Place dough in a greased bowl.
Brush with two tablespoons of melted butter.
Cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator; use as needed.
When made into rolls, let dough rise for about 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Heat the ingredients and season to taste.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Butter the sides and bottom of an 8-inch square cake tin 2-inches deep.
Cream the butter with the sugar; add the egg and beat well.
Add the milk alternately with the dry ingredients sifted together.
Add the berries; mix them in carefully and spread the mixture evenly in the pan.
Top with the following mixture.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
(Does not look done.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine the first 6 ingredients and put in greased casserole. Cut together the oats, salt, margarine or butter and brown sugar with pastry blender. Sprinkle on top of apple mixture and bake for 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands or food processor. Roll into small balls. Bake 15 minutes at 350° or 375°.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In plastic bag, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken pieces in bag, one at a time and shake bag to coat chicken.
Arrange coated chicken in single layer in small shallow roasting dish.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken broth into dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Pour 1/3 cup additional broth over chicken.
Cover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Remove cover.
Baste chicken and bake another 10 minutes. I use bouillon cube, if no broth is available.

title: linda's zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add bread crumbs.
Line bottom of baking dish with this (9 x 13-inch pan will take more crumbs and margarine).
Peel and slice zucchini 1/2-inch thick to cover.
Top with onion slices to cover.
Top with tomato slices to cover. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Italian seasoning.
Cover all with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cover with 2 cups (or more) Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes to melt cheese.
Remove and cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: calzone
directions: Mix garlic and olive oil together and let set for 15 minutes. Steam chicken breast until cooked through.
Cool.
Remove meat, shred or cut into small pieces.
Set aside. Slice sausage links into 1/4 inch thick pieces and saute in pan until done.
Remove from pan and set on paper towel to absorb fat.
Steam green pepper and leeks together.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and crumble sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Layer bread, cheese and sausage in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour egg mixture over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
May add small jar diced pimentos, drained.

title: stan's cheesy catfish
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine cheese, flour
and
seasonings. Dip fish in combined egg and milk and coat
with
flour mixture. Place in baking dish and pour butter over.
Bake for about 45 minutes.
May have to broil last 5 minutes to brown.

title: green olive dip
directions: Chop olives and pecans (not too fine).
Chop onions finely and mix with other ingredients.
Serve chilled on wheat thins.

title: new york roast beef
directions: Rub oil all over roast. Combine garlic and oregano and rub over the oiled roast. Place in shallow baking pan with fat side up.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes per pound. Serving Size: 6 to 7 ounces meat. Exchanges: 7 ounces lean meat, 2 fats.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the cracker crumbs.
Place into a casserole and put the cracker crumbs on the top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix
zucchini,	baking soda, sugar, shortening and egg. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Beat egg and stir in Cool Whip.
Slowly add box of strawberry cake mix.
(This will be difficult to stir; use a wooden spoon.) Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll into balls and then roll balls in powdered sugar.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit filled muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.

title: sweet potato casserole(dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in casserole dish.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator until served.

title: salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix milk, butter, cornstarch, sugar and eggs.
Add creamed corn and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(May be baked in advance and refrigerated.)
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook beans for approximately 8 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and transfer to bowl.
Combine shallots and vinegar gradually. Mix in oil.
Add basil.
Add enough dressing to beans to coat. Gently mix in 2/3 cup cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese.

title: indian recipe - chickpea salad
directions: Pour contents of chickpea cans into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Drain, discarding liquid.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all together and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add cranberries and nuts.
Add juice and shortening, stirring lightly.
Add egg; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased pan.

title: cranberry cornish hens
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, wine and lemon juice in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cranberry sauce melts and mixture is smooth.
Keep warm.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients. Spread the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate pieces.
Spread the chocolate over the peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until firm. Cut into bars.

title: stuff
directions: Coat beef roast with flour and brown in oil.
Pour off oil and add water and the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer until done, about 3 or 4 hours.
Remove beef and vegetables from broth.
Remove fat from broth, leaving about 1 quart broth. Add can undiluted mushroom soup.
Mix and return to simmer. Return beef and vegetables to pot and heat until hot.
Serve over sliced bread for open face sandwiches.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Let set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Stir in other ingredients.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cut squirrels into serving pieces and place in a large kettle with 4 quarts boiling water.
Add salt, onion, beans, corn, potatoes and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add sugar and tomatoes.
Simmer another hour.
Add butter to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil and remove from stove.
Serve with slaw, cornbread and coffee.
(Chicken may be used instead of squirrels.)

title: grecian orange cake
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl; beat at low speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured pan, tube or 11 x 15, and bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: mama's chili sauce
directions: Cook for 3 hours, until thick over medium heat.
Add vinegar the last hour.
Can in pint jars when finished.
Great on burgers!

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in soups and water.
Let simmer 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and crushed graham crackers with hands until stiff.
Make balls.
Melt the chocolate chips with wax.
Dip balls and let cool on wax paper.

title: greek sandwich
directions: Mix olives, chopped onion and about 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt. Saturate well with olive oil.
Cover; let set overnight in refrigerator.
Set oven at 200°.
Slice bread in half lengthwise. On bottom layer, spread all of olive mixture, layer of ham slices, sausage slices, then cheese.
Repeat twice.
Put top on sandwich, then cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.
Slice into sandwich slices and serve warm.

title: french-style green beans
directions: Layer green beans that have been drained (not real dry), a layer of mushroom soup, a layer of beans, ending with soup on top. Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Add onion rings on top, then cover with grated cheese.
Continue to bake until cheese is melted.

title: stir-fried chicken and vegetables
directions: In skillet, heat oil and cook chicken a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.
In same skillet over medium heat, cook vegetables until they are tender-crisp.
In small bowl stir together V-8 juice, cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and ginger.
Gradually stir into vegetables.
Cook until boils. Add chicken and heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in skillet.
When brown, add 1/4 cup water.
In double boiler mix 3/4 cup sugar, milk, egg yolks and flour.
Add brown sugar and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked crust.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix Jell-O and let set until thick.
Whip Cool Whip, then add all the ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Grind bologna, pepperoni and cheese together.
Set aside. Brown hamburg.
Stir in bologna mixture, sauce and salt.
Spread mixture on each half of hamburger bun.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Keeps 1 week in refrigerator or wrap in foil and freeze.

title: sweet orange bread(use a bread oven)
directions: Do not use the delayed bake feature for this recipe.
Use the sweet bake program.
Glaze this bread if you like with powdered sugar and orange juice.

title: blueberry pies
directions: Mix Cool Whip and lemonade, then add Eagle Brand milk (mix). Pour into pie shells.
Top with blueberry pie filling or your choice!
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spinach-mushroom salad
directions: Shake oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic in tightly covered container.
Toss with spinach and mushrooms; sprinkle with bacon and egg.
Serves 8.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir by hand until blended.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar; roll until coated and place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crazy orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, dry gelatin, whipped topping and drained fruit.
May add 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and refrigerate.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch. Add pineapple. Cook until clear and thick over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Let cool. Mix the cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar, salt and eggs.
Add milk and mix thoroughly. Spread pineapple mixture over bottom of unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Pour cream cheese mixture over that. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 50 more minutes. Cool.

title: mick's oreo cheesecake
directions: Remove the cream filling from the Oreos and crush the cookies. Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Press into a 10-inch spring-form pan, and halfway up the side.
Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Roll in 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet, about 3-inches apart.
Press cookies with a fork.
Bake at 375° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: potato pancake
directions: Place mashed potatoes in a bowl. Beat eggs. Add to potatoes along with onion, flour, salt and pepper. Mix well. Heat oil in skillet until hot. Drop potato mixture by ice cream scoop, 1/4 cup at a time, in skillet about 3-inches apart. Flatten with turner. Brown on each side. Serve hot (plain) or with applesauce or maple syrup.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes, with cover on, at 350°.
Add shredded cheese and crumbs; bake 30 minutes longer.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend all ingredients.
(Best if made a day ahead.)
Serve with fresh fruit slices suitable for dipping.

title: steak marinade
directions: Marinate at least one hour.
Use rest to baste meat while cooking.

title: indian-style oven-fried chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine over medium heat. Stir in curry powder and red pepper.
Cook and stir for 1 minute. Set aside.
In a blender container or a food processor combine peanuts and coconut.
Blend or process until peanuts are ground. Transfer mixture to a pie plate or shallow mixing bowl.
Stir in cornmeal, paprika and salt.
Set aside.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Spray bottom of a wok with cooking spray.
Cook vegetables first.
It will take about 15 to 20 minutes.
While this is being done, you can cook your rice.
After vegetables are done, set aside and place your chicken in wok.
Wok needs to be very hot for chicken.
You may need to spray again with cooking spray before putting chicken in.
Season chicken with soy sauce as you cook it. You need to stir chicken often as you cook it.
It will take about 5 to 8 minutes to cook.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan.
Place cherry in each slice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups.
Add this and 2 eggs to cake mix and mix as directed.
Pour into pan over pineapple and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes in pan before removing.

title: wakefield holiday dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix in lemon juice, chopped onions, mustard and garlic powder.
Fold in Snow crabmeat or Snow crabmeat and shrimp.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups of dip.

title: chicken parts
directions: Mix and add to chicken parts.
Bake in casserole 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, adding sugar and salt until stiff.
Add nuts, vanilla and chocolate.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
In preheated 350° oven, place cookies on cookie sheets and turn off oven.
Keep oven door closed and leave overnight.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pork chop and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pork chops aside.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread evenly in baking pan.
Lay pork chops on top and bake 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook the hen until tender.
Shred or chop the meat.
Make a sauce of the sour cream, onions (sauteed in butter first), salt, cooked and drained spinach (reserve juice), chilies, spinach water and milk.
Mix some of the sauce with the diced chicken.
Fill and roll the tortillas.
Cover with grated Monterey Jack cheese and top with remaining sauce.
Bake until hot through at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend together Ricotta and cream cheese.
Add sugar, mix well. Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition on high speed.
Reduce speed to medium, slowly add cornstarch, lemon juice, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Add sour cream, mix well. Pour into greased and dusted with graham cracker crumbs spring-form pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Turn oven off and let sit in oven for 2 hours until cool.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix biscuit mix, butter and pumpkin pie spice well.
Add eggs and rum flavoring and beat well.
Add milk and pumpkin and mix well.

title: cheesy fries
directions: Heat everything except fries and shredded cheese until cheese melts.
Place 1/2 bag of fries in a 6 x 11-inch casserole dish. Pour half of cheese mixture on top.
Add remaining French fries and top with second half of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/4 hours. Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown on top.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese slowly over warm water. Stir in browned sausage.
Add biscuit mix and stir.
Shape into bite size balls.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dill okra
directions: Put in bottom of jar
the
garlic,
hot pepper and dill seed, then pack okra in
jar.
Boil
vinegar,
water and salt; pour over okra in jar and seal.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 cup Wesson oil, 1 1/2 teaspoons dry mustard and 1 1/2 teaspoons paprika in order given.
Beat with rotary egg beater for 3 minutes by the clock.
Add remaining ingredients and put in quart jar. Cover lightly and shake well for about 5 minutes.
Keep in cool place.

title: day ahead salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: menudo
directions: Cut cleaned and thoroughly washed tripe into slices about 1-inch wide and cook 1 hour in a large pot with water.
Add the hominy, onion, garlic, salt and oregano.
Simmer 6 to 7 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put the water and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix the water, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Pour into boiled mixture and boil until thick and clear.
Add the food coloring. Cool and pour in the strawberries.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
pour	over chicken, which has been placed in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at
Remove
foil	and
bake
for 15 minutes uncovered.	Serve with rice.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except flour, until creamy.
Add flour, a small amount at a time, until smooth.
Roll into small balls; place on baking sheet.
Press with a fork, dipped in water, crosswise.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chunky beef-fritters
directions: Mix milk with 1 tablespoon of flour and stir into eggs.
Mix together flour, black pepper and salt.
Dip roast beef chunk in egg mixture and roll in flour mixture.
Drop floured beef chunks into hot cooking oil and deep fry until brown (use medium heat).
Drain and serve hot.
Takes about 15 minutes and yields 4 to 6 servings (time does not include cooking time for roast).
Serve on divided serving dish surrounded by pickles, crab apple or cherry tomatoes, green pepper rings, carrot curls, celery sticks and parsley.
Vary garnishes according to your taste.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In frying pan, brown chicken in oil. Once it is brown, put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sweet and sour sauce and drained pineapple chunks over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 40 minutes covered, then 5 minutes uncovered.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop 1 teaspoon batter per cookie onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: pear salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Refrigerate to thicken slightly.
Whip with electric beater or blender.
Whip in jello, cheese, pears and Cool Whip in that order.
Add nuts on top. Chill.
